name: Spacious apt with the best rooftop in Condesa
description:
This is a lovely apartment in Condesa. You'll love spending time on the day-beds, and having fun with Argentinian grill and wood-fired pizza oven. It features a dedicated work space and has potential to host more guests if needed for short stays. It even has a private mini patio.
We just completed renovations on the apartment and the place looks better than ever!

The space
The place is ideal for a singles or couples. Up to two children can also be accommodated but bear in mind there is only one bathroom. It has a fully equipped kitchen with a gas stove with oven, fridge, appliances and utensils. Wireless High-Speed internet, premium Cable TV package featuring HBO and Netflix. Everything is taken care off so that all you need to bring is your suit case!

Guest access
Guests will have the entire apartment to their personal use. Common areas like our beautiful roof garden and laundry room will be shared with other guests and tenants

name: Contemporary House with Jacuzzi in San Angel
description:
Gorgeous Contemporary House in San Angel, designed by architect Bernardo Gómez Pimienta, with contemporary art and top comfort.
Miele kitchen appliances, heated floors, walking closet, jacuzzi , access to our shared and beautiful Roof-deck with BBQ, fire pit and water fall.

The space
The property is settled in a cobblestone street two steps away from the shopping street Altavista where luxury shops and restaurants are willing to help you find what you are looking for.
Our house with garage starts with a Patio and a contemporary wooden wall as a façade. Two bedrooms are in the ground floor with a sharing bathroom with tub. Then upstairs is the social area with the kitchen fully equipped, the living room and the dining area too. On the top level the main room has a walking closet and a bathroom with jacuzzi. Outside the room there is a corridor to the roofDeck. When you are out, first you pass by the green house, and then you get to the BBQ area and after
host_about:
We are a mexican couple who has been together for more than 25 years. We have two teenagers: a daughter, a son.
We are in the IT business and we love to travel. We always travel as if it was the last trip of our lives. For us, family, love and harmony are essential in life. We enjoy contemporary art and we are dedicated to promoting mexican artists and culture in every place we visit. 
Pancho and I met scuba diving in 1994, therefore the sea, nature and outdoor activities are basic and necessary. We enjoy camping, scuba diving and sailing, sport in which we compete every month in Acapulco.
Lunch time is a special moment for us, a pause where we can enjoy and celebrate being together, a moment apart from the rush of the city where we prepare ourselves for the afternoon daily commitments.
We love Mexico and we are ambassadors of our country, we always talk about how great is the mexican spirit, its culture, gastronomy, nature, beaches and its history. If we had to choose another country to live, it would be Italy for the same reasons we love Mexico.
We recognize ourselves as entrepreneurs because of our professional upbringing, we generate projects and ideas, some of which become business ventures. We've always been motivated by the risk, investing time, money and effort to develop new ideas with a purposeful end. Another factor deeply rooted in our family is ecology and self sustainability and seek to have the least possible impact on our environment and our planet .
We have a francophile part because the 4 of Pancho's grandparents were born in France and married in Mexico . With some friends, we spontaneously create an amateur theater group fifteen years ago, "Théâtre a la Dérive", where we enjoy making plays in French just for the pleasure of the whole process, costumes, learning the script and friendship. The group is composed mainly by frenchies living in México.
Today what bring us here is that 14 years ago, on a sabathical year, we lived in a "Chateau" in France countryside, and we opened 11 rooms to host our beloved...  more than a hundred friends and family members came to visit and stayed with us in that 12th century castle. The uniqueness of this experience led us to replicate the model in Mexico, and we open our home with a project: Art Residence to share it with you, people with similar interests, that want to enjoy living among art in our village of San Angel,  town founded 500 years ago and today immersed in one of the largest and most exciting cities in the world: Mexico City. Welcome!

In our country we say to our guests: "Mi casa es tu casa. My home is your home".

neiborhood_overview:
San Ángel is a XVI century village nestled in the big Mexico City: its architecture is lovely and still preserve beautiful houses and gardens, and its safe to walk around its unique small alleys and secret spots.

During the Viceroyalty in the XVI - XVIII centuries, San Angel was the perfect place for country homes to rest close to the city.

Walking distance, you will find several museums as the Carrillo Gil Modern Art Museum, the Diego Rivera and Frida Kahlo Studio Museum, the gorgeous Ex-Convento del Carmen Museum, the Mexican Revolutions Museum, la Casa del Risco or the Isidro Fabela House.

You cannot miss the Bazaar del Sábado, on Saturdays... just 2 blocks away in Plaza San Jacinto, where local artists and all-around-the-country handcrafts market promenade is really enjoyable.

Other nice neighborhoods as Coyoacan or Chimalistac, and the main campus of UNAM (National University) are close enough to visit plenty of cultural spots as the fa

name: PLAZA DEL ARCÁNGEL EN SAN ÁNGEL
description:
The space
Preciosa casa tipo colonial, ubicada en el tradicional barrio de San Ángel, a dos cuadras del Bazar del Sábado. Calle empedrada, tranquila y con vigilancia. Buena ubicación, cercana a Metrobus y Metro.
Barrio tranquilo ideal para caminar, buena oferta de restaurantes, cultura e historia.
La casa cuenta con 3 habitaciones, 3 y medio baños, escritorio-biblioteca, sala TV, gimnasio, terrazas, hermoso jardín, sala con chimenea, comedor, cocina equipada con lavatrastes, estacionamiento, Internet Wi-Fi, lavadora y secadora de ropa. Se renta con persona encargada para cuidado y aseo que vive allí. La renta puede ser con o sin deyauno (a pactar).
host_about:
Me gusta ser honesta porque es lo que espero de los demás hacia mí. Disfruto de la gente y la armonía de la naturaleza y los espacios. La música, el arte, una buena conversación, una caminata, un buen vino y la comida también son muy preciados para mí.
Estudié unos años de arquitectura, me gradué de sociología con un posgrado en desarrollo urbano. Creo que la transformación del mundo generada por el sistema actual, exige una toma de conciencia y la re-construcción de un mundo posible para todos y entre todos.
Lo que más me molesta es la injusticia y la mentira.
Me encanta bailar.
Viajar me parece siempre una oportunidad maravillosa para conocer y aprender sobre otras culturas que forman parte de nosotros mismos.
Cuando viajo me gusta alojarme en un espacio luminoso, limpio y alegre, ojalá en contacto o cerca de la naturaleza, con vistas hermosas. No me gustan los espacios cerrados, oscuros y con demasiados adornos. Disfruto de cada pieza antigua (especialmente) o rústica pero en equilibrio.
Disfruto en general de la buena mesa: la comida mexicana, la peruana, la francesa, la china; comer bien siempre será un buen panorama para mí.
Me interesa la historia, los problemas de la actualidad, escuchar a la gente.
No tengo lema en la vida, creo que eso sería limitarla y desconocer lo vasta y misteriosa que es. No pretendo decirme conocedora de ella.

host_about: I am a mother, documentary film maker and photo curator, originally from England but today live in  Mexico City. Coyoacan is an amazing neighborhood and it gives me pleasure in introducing our guests to places I have discovered over time. name: HOUSE INDIGO IN THE CEN. OF MEX CITY
description:
The space
This House is located in a real mexican neighborhood, it's 15 min. walking from "Alameda Central" ,Bellas Artes and Zocalo , 5 min. walking from "Monumento a la Revolución" and Avenue Reforma. An Casa Indigo in the middle of all the sightseeings in the Historical Center of Mexico City. Also we offer tours inside downtown and a bike tour every Sunday through Av. Reforma . Museo de Antropología and Bosque de Chapultepec !

We have bakery, supermarkets and local food markets around the corner. Our place is located inside a block of 5 houses , for that there is less noise of cars.

HIDALGO ( Blue Line number 2 ) and GUERRERO ( Green and gray line , Line B)

DELEGACIÓN CUAUHTEMOC, one station before the last of that Line that
host_about:
I studied Industrial Design at UNAM (the public University in Mexico City) after that I lived one year in Buenos Aires Argentina and then 5 months in Paris, France  and 3 months in Berlin, Germany.  I usually work in culture and projects with photography and women's rights, at the moment I'm helping to built the Association  of (Website hidden by Airbnb)  and refreshing the website. 

I like travel and be honest !

My last travel was in India and was really good ...

I know my city so I can recommend you lot's of things to do :)

Historical house in the heart of colonial neighborhood San Angel. There is Wi-fi available, a car can safely park on the streets outside, and towels and bed sheets will be provided. We can also provide delicious continental breakfast if you'd like us to.

neiborhood_overview:
Mexico City can be a nightmare but it can also be paradise. It really just depends on where you go and where you stay.
This house is literally next to a forest in probably the cleanest and most modern neighborhood and area of all Mexico City. My parents bought this house decades ago, back then we were the only house besides a horse farm and a pig farmer. Now, this beautiful piece of forest and green land has been constructed with modern and beautiful condos and houses. The neighborhood has the highest quality of life in all of Mexico City. Huge shopping malls with stores, groceries, nightlife, restaurants etc. are all withing 10-15 minutes drive. And the biggest plus: our garden and a huge forest right in front of our door. You can breathe clean air (which is a rarity in Mexico City), or go running and walking in the forest. It's basically European life style in Mexico City.

name: Sweet studio
description:
Self contained studio in a lovely house. Kind hosts happy to help you find your way around the city. // Pequenio estudio independiente en casa. Anfitriones amables felices de ayudarte con direcciones para moverte por la ciudad.

The space
Lovely new studio with bathroom, kitchenette and wooden wardrobe. // Precioso nuevo estudio con banio, cocineta y closet de madera.

Other things to note
Minimum stay 5 nights.// Minima estadia 5 noches.

If you are coming to DF to study or work for a long period, check our weekly and monthly rates. // Si vienes al DF a estudiar o a trabajar, checa nuestras tarifa semanal y mensual.
host_about:
I am a keen traveller and I find inspiration to my journeys through literature. When I am reading I get to picture how people used to live in previous times in different countries and cities. Through literature I have learned about the old trading routes and the first merchant journeys to Japan and now I really want to go there. I am currently reading a war story based in Turkey and Egypt, the descriptions of Alexandria, its streets and smells really make me want to go there.  

I am constantly in the search of experiencing and learning from new cultures. I have recently started learning Tango. I find it fascinating to learn about a new culture through their art and lifestyle. It is also a brilliant conversation topic which gives an opportunity to talk to people. 

I am interested in fashion and design. It is important to me to look presentable and well put together, the same goes to my home and I also look for similar places to stay when I travel. 

If I get to stay at your place I would look after it and water your plants if you have some. I would respect the house rules and ensure you are happy to host me at your home.

neiborhood_overview:
El barrio mágico de Coyoacán esta ubicado en el corazón de la Ciudad. Dentro de él se encuentran las sedes de importantes instituciones educativas de México, como la Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México y la Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana. Alberga recintos tan importantes como los museos Nacional de las Intervenciones, el Anahuacalli, el Nacional de la Acuarela y el Centro Cultural Universitario.

El centro histórico de Coyoacán es uno de los barrios intelectuales y bohemios de la capital mexicana. Con excelente oferta cultural gastronomica y de entretenimiento. Numerosos personajes públicos nacionales y extranjeros artistas como Frida Kahlo y Diego Rivera, intelectuales y políticos, han tenido su residencia en sus alrededores.

The neighborhood is mostly residential and very safe, but that doesn't mean it lacks food and entertainment options! A few blocks away from the house you can find various types of restaurants from typical mexican "comida corrida" spots, to sushi, hamburgers, bakeries and multiple street food carts. Also a few blocks away we have a big shopping mall, super markets and many public transportation stops that can take you to the typical touristic destinations.
For students, Tec de Monterrey University is a 5 minute bus ride, as well as UAM and even UVM has it's South campus nearby.
For more traditionally touristic destinations, we are closely located to the famous Xochimilco neighborhood where you can ride typical trajineras while listening to floating mariachi bands and eating mexican street food.
If you have questions or are interested in specific locations please don't hesitate to ask me!

name: BEAUTIFUL/UNIQUE Apt❤️ Private ROOF GARDEN & more!
description:
BEAUTIFUL PENTHOUSE APARTMENT! Stay at this SUNNY Apartment, with a Gorgeous ROOF GARDEN and a WONDERFUL VIEW OF THE PLAZA! Located in a SAFE, Trendy DOWNTOWN NEIGHBORHOOD close to MEXICO CITY'S Historic Center. FULLY-EQUIPPED: Bedroom with ULTRA KING-SIZE BED, Cozy Living Room W/Futon, Kitchenette, INTERNET, Cable TV. CLOSE TO EVERYTHING: Top Museums, Theaters, Restaurants, Cafes, Hip Bars and Trendy Shops. Truly, a MOST UNIQUE SPOT, in the HEART of Mexico City. YOU'LL REALLY LOVE IT!!!

The space
This is a unique and charming apartment, in an ideal downtown location, close to top cafes, restaurants, museums, shopping centers and public transportation. This well-kept apartment is full of light, comfortable and an ideal place to rest in between your business or pleasure outings. Enjoy the bedroom with its comfortable king-sized bed; take advantage of the apartment's Mexican rustic styled kitchen; lounge in the cozy living room with internet access and cable tv
host_about: I am a marriage and family counselor with a private practice. Born in New York City I married a Mexican National from Mexico City and lived in the DF for 30 years.  We also lived in El Paso, TX.  Now we're back in Mexico City. I am bi-cultural and bi-lingual.  I love Mexico´s cultural life and am a lover of opera and classical music.  I also love to read and have many books of contemporary literature and fiction in my library.  And finally, I love to cook and am famous among friends and colleagues for nurturing through food. I spend a lot of time in this big, sunny and wonderful house and neighborhood, which has become trendy and is right in the middle of art galleries, boutiques, restaurants, markets, and public transportation. The airbnb apartment I rent is completely independent. It is clean and beautiful and will offer you a wonderful stay in a unique and marvelous spot of the city.

I will be very glad to help you enjoy this contrasting beloved city.

name: Casa de campo con vista a la Cd. Mx
description:
Cabaña ecológica en el Ajusco con impresionante vista a la Cd de Mexico.
Excelente para pasar un fin de semana fuera de la ciudad, relajarse en el campo, disfrutar el aire limpio y alejarse del estrés diario.
IMPORTANTE:
La cabaña NO cuenta con Luz está en un área protegida,
NO hay señal de celular pero cuenta con los demás servicios (Agua, Gas, telefono fijo y proveemos unas velas para iluminar en la noche).
Consideren que la cabaña se encuentra a cerca de 3,000 m.s.n.m.

The space
La cabaña se encuentra dentro de un terreno privado cercado y rodeada de arboles. En el terreno hay diferentes animales que estan en sus jaulas, donde los huespedes, si tienen interés pueden observa e interactuar con ellos (Ganzos, guajolote, gallinas, patos y palomas mensajeras). El aire limpio y la tranquilidad que ofrece la cabaña es ideal para un fin de semana con 0 estres, ya sea haciendo una carne asada en el asador enfrente de la cabaña o cocinando algo
host_about: Hola!!! Mi nombre es Susana! Vivo en la ciudad de México! Soy muy atenta y me gusta mucho viajar y hospedar a la gente en la cabana que tenemos en el ajusco.

neiborhood_overview:
"Condesa" or "La Condesa" consists of three "colonias" or officially recognized neighborhoods: Colonia Condesa, Colonia Hipódromo and Colonia Hipódromo Condesa. The area is considered to be fashionable and popular with younger business people, artists, students and intellectuals. It features a large number of international restaurants and nightclubs, despite the fact that it is mostly residential.

Condesa and neighboring Colonia Roma were together designated as a "Barrio Mágico Turístico" ("Magic Neighborhood for Tourists") by the city in 2011.

You can find more information by searching the Internet.

name: ROMA LOVELY HOUSE,  BEST LOCATION
description:
Beautiful Porfirian house protected by fine arts, cozy, clean and safe in the heart of Colonia Roma, one of the most important cultural centers of Mexico City, known for its big social life, art galleries, restaurants, wooded areas, boutiques.

The space
The house facade remains as original form early twentieth century, only has 4 departments, despite the time the place is in perfect condition as new, on the ground floor is the kitchen with all the necessary tools, living room and dining room, some of the furniture that you'll find there, are original form the period. On the first floor there is beautiful brightly bedroom, a comfortable queen-size bed, dresser with mirror, closet, bathroom. It has every detail to make comfort your stadia, the entire department is very comfortable and clean, has cable TV and Wi-Fi.
MASTER BEDROOM: Queen Size bed.
GUEST BED: Queen Size sofa bed.

Check in: 14-21hrs

neiborhood_overview:
Colonia Roma is one of the most important and secure cultural centers of Mexico City, known for its big social life and architecture form the beginning of XIX Century, it is home form many artists and art galleries, wooded areas, supermarkets, malls and open spaces to enjoy. You will be able to find many activities on the day and night. It is located a few blocks from La Condesa, near Downtown and Polanco.

La colonia Roma es uno de los centros culturales más importantes y seguros de la ciudad de México, reconocida por su inmensa vida social y arquitectura de principios de siglo, es hogar de gran número de artistas por lo que abundan las galerías de arte, zonas arboladas, plazas y espacios que disfrutar. Podrás encontrar numerosas actividades en el día y por la noche. Se encuentra a pocas calles de La Condesa, muy cerca del centro histórico de la ciudad y de Polanco.

Lovely old colonial house located in one of the main streets that access the center of Coyoacan. 100m2 in one floor completely and recently remodeled, vintage furnished. The nearest subway station is 10min walking distance and the trolleybus station is 5mins. Since it is an old house it does not have garage but there is a public parking lot 15m away.

The space
100m2 in one floor completely and recently remodeled, vintage furnished. The house has one bedroom with a queen size bed. A small bathroom with hot/cold water shower. A very nice living room with a sofa that turns into a comfortable full size bed. The kitchen has all the basic stuff you need to cook. name: Gorgeous Condesa House with Beautiful Private Garden
description:
This gorgeous, recently renovated 1920's home features its own private garden, a welcome green oasis in the bustling metropolis of Mexico City. Spend the morning exploring the neighborhood, then retire for a siesta or afternoon coffee on the terrace.

This house is the residence of a travel writer and her partner, a renowned Spanish artist. Once owned by Mexico’s Secretary of Education, Jaime Torres Bodet (a founder of our world famous Anthropology Museum) it has been painstakingly restored by the current owners in keeping with the true essence of the property, while adding a personal touch with furniture, objects and art they have collected from all over the world.

This is one of the few houses in Mexico with European central heating. ( a must to have during winter )

The house has two stories and a mezzanine. On the main floor is the living room with original chimney and wood floors, kitchen, and dining room that seats 8 people and looks onto a peace
host_about:
I am an inveterate world traveler and culture vulture. I travel for pleasure and work (writing, collecting local art, antiques, and crafts for shops and museums) I love yoga, scuba diving, art, local food, exploring museums, indigenous art, and hiking with my rescued dog Jet. I divide my time between Madrid, Los Angeles,  Mexico City, and the world.
  My style of traveling is staying in a historical building or a beautiful home with the local touch.   I love classical music, jazz, Cuban, ethnic music. I love reading local authors of the places where I go.  I like living a healthy life style.

name: Casa José Clemente Orozco Coyoacán
description:
Located in Coyoacán, typical Mexican neighborhood surrounded by markets, museums and historical buildings, a few blocks from Museu Frida Khalo, this house was the first studio for the painter and muralist José Clemente Orozco, who designed and build it between 1921 and 1923.
All the bedrooms have their own bathroom and the main suite has a king-size bed, Smart TV and a terrace.
It has a big and beautiful garden and a work space with its own terrace too.
The garden is shared by 2 houses.

The space
Beautifull 3 suites house designed by José Clemente Orozco.
The main suite has its own terrace with cofee table, king-size bed and 2 side tables with lamps, 40 inches Smart tv, balcony over the garden, work space, swing-chair and full closet.
The second suite has a queen-size bed and 2 side tables with lamps, full size closet, wondefull view to the garden, and wi-fi acces.

Somos dos hermanas que disfrutamos conocer gente de todo el mundo y compartir la historia de nuestro bisabuelo, el muralista José Clemente Orozco, quién contruyó su estudio en esta Casa. 

We are sisters that enjoy meeting people around the world and sharing the history of our great grandfather the muralist Jose Clemente Orozco, who built his studio in this property.

name: CASA DELFINO 5 BED 3SH BATH
description:
Beautiful house in the Condesa, built in 1937. Recently restored and redecorated.
It has five bedrooms, three bathrooms and all services. Fully functional. Located in a very quiet street, but conveniently close to all kinds of restaurants, bars, cafes and beautiful parks, among many other attractions. Great for families or groups of friends up to 10 guests.

The space
The house has 5 bedrooms, 4 of them with king size beds and the remaining one with a queen size bed. All rooms have closets and safety box.
Four rooms have a work table.
In the common area we have a desk with multiple drawers, to work comfortably.
A full bathroom with toilet, sink and shower on the ground floor and 2 full bathrooms also upstairs.
Full kitchen including gas oven and laundry center.

Guest access
The house is absolutely private for the guests. You can access the backyard and enjoy the garden table.

neiborhood_overview:
La Colonia Roma is proud to be, along with Condesa, the first housing division with all the necessary infrastructure services. There were three factors that distinguished her from her contemporaries.

In the first instance, the urban area is notable, with its notable innovations: wide streets with ridges (Orizaba), tree-lined avenues of Veracruz, today Insurgentes (30 meters), and Jalisco, today Álvaro Obregón (45 meters) Boulevard parisino The nomenclature of its streets, like the Countess, uses the names of states and cities of the Mexican Republic. Two squares were drawn on the north-south central axis of the colony: Parque Roma (Plaza Rio de Janeiro), and Plaza Ajusco (Luis Cabrera).

The second factor is its architecture, as it was built the last buildings in the art nouveau, eclectic and French style that characterized the regime of Porfirio Diaz. There are still about 1,500 buildings already converted into artistic monuments.

neiborhood_overview:
El departamento está ubicado en una zona histórica. Se encuentra enfrente de la Ciudadela, donde ocurrió el suceso de la Decena Trágica al presidente Francisco I. Madero e Ignacio Pino Suárez. En el lugar se encuentra el monumento que indica el acontecimiento acontecido en 1913. A un costado está la Biblioteca México que contiene las bibliotecas personales de personajes destacados de la cultura mexicana como Antonio Castro Leal, Alí Chumacero y Carlos Monsiváis. En su tiempo fue la sede de la Armería mexicana.
En la esquina del departamento se ubica el Mercado de Artesanías de la Ciudadela. Lugar ideal para comprar productos típicos mexicanos. Ahí es posible adquirir cualquier artesanía de la ciudad o de cualquier región del país.
También a unos pocos metros se encuentra la Avenida Bucareli celebre por ser uno de los paseos históricos diseñados a principios del siglo XIX. Destaca el Reloj Chino, Café la Habana, la fachada de los periódicos El Universal y Excélsior.
Igual

name: Just Refreshed -  Secluded - Patio and Terrace
description:
This house has a vintage character. The high ceilings make the space bigger, the house orientation and the oversize windows provide very good light. The house is very quiet and intimate the patio and the terrace are perfect for enjoying the mild weather of the city. The location forms a triangle with the Condesa and Roma Norte being 2 blocks from Insurgentes street and half block from Medellin market. The deco is intentionally sober to create a relaxing environment.

The space
The house is on ground level with the benefit of spacious rooms. The kitchen and the dinning room have access thru the patio. Ideal for three and comfortable for five as well, this is an independent space but in combination with house on the front (1920 tile house I) could be a excellent place for a big group travelling together.

The main bedroom has a queen bed and a walking closet, this room has a little patio on the back that works as a private relaxing space.

The
host_about:
I will treat my guest as I would like to be treated when I travel making their experience an enjoyable one. 

The places I offer are meant to be comfortable, clean and have specific locations for visiting the city. Every place is unique and it has been thought for enjoyment of the guests.

La colonia San Rafael tiene una ubicación privilegiada. Se encuentra a 20 minutos caminando de Reforma (Ángel de la Independencia y Reforma 222). La estación del metro más cercano está a 3 calles (Metro San Cosme línea azul) la cual te lleva al Centro Histórico y a Bellas Artes en 6 estaciones o menos. El Monumento a la Revolución y Plaza de la República está a una parada o puedes llegar caminando. El Museo de San Carlos está también caminando del depto. La colonia Santa María la Ribera, una colonia también emergente y con mucha historia, famosa por su quiosco morisco está junto a la San Rafael. La Condesa y la Roma quedan a 10 minutos en Uber o a 20 minutos en bicicleta.



La colonia es una zona tranquila, bien vigilada, que está dándose a conocer por su variada oferta cultural de galerías de talla internacional y galerías emergentes de arte contemporáneo, residencias de artistas, centros culturales, museos, restaurantes, cafeterías y arquitectura de la época por

name: Elegant Art Deco Home with Garden in Condesa
description:
Enjoy the elegance of a by-gone era while staying in this Art Deco home. Beautifully decorated and featuring a sweeping staircase, original stained glass windows, period furniture, and a stunningly unique black-and-white tiled bathroom.

The house is located on a green walkway in La Condesa and counts various living rooms, dining rooms, three bedrooms, three bathrooms, a garden, a rooftop terrace and a study room, which is a separated work space with sunlight, internet connection and private bathroom.

Our art deco home has been lovingly curated to reflect the era, but we also have had all mod-cons. You can relax in our iconic deco bathroom and feel like a film star, while watching a movie online. We have a fully equipped kitchen, a large dining room, a living room, wifi in the house and a closed garden. Our home sleeps 5 people in 3 bedrooms, one king size bed, two singles in one room and a third with a single bed and 3 bathrooms.
We have off street parking,
host_about: De padre francés y madre húngara,he pasado mi infancia viajando  entre Europa y America Latina,pero elegimos Mexico para establecernos. Aunque soy diseñadora de modas de profesión (tengo una tienda /taller en la Roma donde realizamos todo tipo de prendas únicas,sobre medida y al gusto del cliente) me apasiona la arquitectura,en particular el Art Deco.Hemos cuidado y restaurado todos los elementos originales de la casa,las lamparas y muchos muebles que son parte de la casa.tenemos muchos artistas en la familia.Mi hermana ,es fotógrafa.Mi pareja ,artista contemporáneo.Mi suegro y mi cuñado son (Website hidden by Airbnb) gusta mucho leer,así que hay una gran variedad de literatura en la casa,desde novela negra,clásica,autores (Website hidden by Airbnb) encanta el viaje pero me gusta también recibir y compartir el Mexico que conozco y el que me apasiona.

name: Casa Grande en San Miguel Chapultepec
description:
Hermosa casa grande con precioso jardin, para hasta 9 personas en la bella San Miguel Chapultepec. Una isla de silencio y paz en medio de la gran Metropolis

The space
At the end of the 19th century, Tacubaya, now San Miguel Chapultepec, was a small town very close to the center of Mexico City, an area of large country houses. This was one of them.
With the growth of the city, many of these houses were demolished, to make way for great avenues. So it happened with part of this house.
With what was left , in1960, our parents built
three houses around a large garden.

Several trees and at least 50% of the furniture, are from around the end of the 19th century.
The house consists of an entrance hall, a dining room, two living rooms and a large garden on the ground floor.
On the upper floor are , four very spacious bedrooms (two to the street and two to the garden), each with its own bathroom, and a hall. You arrive to

name: 1930's house and garden in Escandon
description:
Beautiful fully equipped restored historic 1930’s house. An urban oasis. the patio has an inverted garden sculpture and Pomegranate trees! you can pick from the herbal garden fresh mint, rosemary, basel for your everyday use. There are Flowers all year long thank to the luscious plants that grow in the patio.

The bedroom is quiet and cosy. You can start your mornings, by opening the door into the Patio.

Next door there is a construction, work goes between 8 am and 6 pm .

The space
The house is decorated and owned by an artist couple and is ideal for a couple that enjoys exploring the vibrant modern and historical city, food lover, architecture passionate, flaneur, artistic, or contemplative person. Some of the rooms are for working place so they will be closed while you stay.
Its a very large house so there plenty of outdoor and indoor to enjoy 😉 😉
The facade have graffiti , so you may notice new ones during your stay.

name: 3br in Historic Mansion Steps from the Cathedral
description:
Architecturally important 17th century palace. This grand home sleeps up to 8 guests in 3 beautifully decorated, en-suite bedrooms and offers butler service.

Delight in the use of this historical family manor, carefully restored with a prestigious art collection. Pricing for all three bedrooms for your family or friends with gorgeous views of the Cathedral and Zocalo. Close to museums, dining & shopping. Contact us for single bedroom pricing.

The space
The house on Seminario 12 is built on top of the remains of the Ceremonial Center of the Aztec City of Tenochtitlán. The land was subdivided by Hernán Cortés and adjudicated to one of his lieutenants, Pedro de Maya However, the construction of the house as it can be seen now, dates 1626.

This family residence belonged to two of the oldest estates of the Spanish colony, to that of Hernando de Avila during the first years of the century, and to the López de Peralta estate between 1624 and 175

neiborhood_overview:
La Condesa is one of the 'trendiest' areas in Mexico City and also one of the safest. It's full of great wee places to explore on foot including a wealth of bars, restaurants, cafes, galleries and shops.
Parque México and España are great for wandering around or exercising - both have free open air gym facilities and jogging tracks - and are the perfect option if you have kids as they both have excellent play parks and are just 100 meters from the apartment.
If you fancy a bit more of an adventure the massive Chapultepec park is just 1km away, it's brilliant for running, walking, cycling or visiting the museums and huge free zoo inside it.
Roma neighbourhood is also just a stone's throw away which is another great neighbourhood, that's where you'll find Mercado Medellin, our favourite market for all things food related.

neiborhood_overview:
STRATEGICALLY SITUATED between Roma, Condesa and Juarez, 3 of the most cool & vibrant neighborhoods in the city.

3 BLOCKS AWAY from “Reforma Av.” (the most beautiful avenue of the city) that leads directly to downtown, and which is venue of diverse cultural and artistic exhibitions.

5 MINUTES WALKING from “Chapultepec Park” (one of the most important green areas of the city) which offers a great amount of outdoor activities.

EXCELLENT LOCATION for tourism because you can walk to the main turistic attractions: Anthropology Museum, Tamayo Museum, Modern Art Museum, Chapultepec Castle, Independence Monument, Cibeles Fountain, etc.

IDEAL LOCATION for business trips as well, due to its proximity to the main financial avenues of the city (Reforma and Insurgentes), where there are big office skyscrapers. In addition, there are 2 co-working spaces at less than a block (one right in the corner, and the other crossing the street).

GREAT LOC

name: Fantastic home with garden in Mexico City downtown
description:
This 2 floors house is centrally located between the historic center (15 mns), the trendy neighborhood of Polanco and La condesa (10 mns). Located in a quiet street, it is just 2 blocks from the major landmark of the city "El Angel de la Independencia" . The house with its garden, terraces and fountain is an oasis in the middle of the busy city. Its european style architecture filled with mexican artwork and sculptures can host 5 people in a cozy 260 m2.

The space
The House is one of the few houses remaining in the neighborhood , 2 blocks from Reforma Ave, the main avenue in Mexico City. The Garden, the tile roof, the chimenea and the Artwork give to the place an unique atmosphere in the center of the city. Ideally located, It is close to lots of restaurants and bars.

neiborhood_overview:
Coyoacan or ‘the place of coyotes,’ is in the south of Mexico City, full colorful houses that the Spanish conquistadors built after the Aztec Empire was defeated. Cortés chose to settle in the south of Tenochtitlan, Coyoacan's neighborhood today, where later Frida Kahlo and Diego Rivera lived. It is also known for its Franciscan ex-monastery, downtown squares, markets, cantinas, coffee shops.

Close-by attractions:

Chimalistac
Viveros de Coyoacán
Mercado de Coyoacan
Museo Diego Rivera Anahuacalli
Frida Kahlo’s blue house
Cineteca Nacional
Capilla de la Conchita

name: Luxury Loft in San Angel- 1BR Queen/1BA
description:
20% OFF !!!
Welcome to San Angel: Mexico City's most stylish and charming neighbourhood. We look forward hosting you in our beautiful home. Luxury Loft ready for your arrival (fresh linen, fully equipped kitchen), cable TV, wifi, washer/dryer. Spacious layout in two levels with 1 bedroom and 1 bathroom, open concept kitchen, spacious living rooom and patio. Sleep 2 people, 1 Queen size bed and armchair. Located in a quiet street a few steps away from main avenues. Secured underground parking.
host_about: My name is Juan Gabriel Solorzano and I am a Mexican Architecht who has lived in San Angel all his life. I know this neighbourhood well, and it is with great pride that I welcome guests here. As an architect, I pay special attention to the design and functionality of space. I trust you will find in my place a combination of comfort and elegance. I particularly enjoy landscape architecture and have built lush gardens into my properties.  What I like most form Airbnb is the opportunity to show guests a little bit of the Mexico that I love.

San Angel is a quiet and charming town inside Mexico City. Pebble-stoned narrow streets, colonial houses, parks, plazas, colonial churches, museums and many other destinations make it a must stop in your visit to Mexico City.

San Angel is a quiet and charming town inside Mexico City. Pebble-stoned narrow streets, colonial houses, parks, plazas, colonial churches, museums and many other destinations make it a must stop in your visit to Mexico City.

Mexico City’s Secretary of Tourism recently named the San Angel neighborhood a Barrio Magico (Magic Neighborhood). San Angel, located 12km (7.4 miles) southwest of the historic center, was once a retreat for wealthy city residents. Cobblestone streets, plazas, gardens and elegant estates are reminiscent of the neighborhood’s rich colonial past.

San Angel is home to monuments, historic residences, a former Dominican monastery, a cultural center housed in what was once a municipal palace and several interesting

name: Classic 1930's Condesa house with beautiful patio
description:
Classic two-floor Condesa house from the 1930's, in one of the most iconic streets in the neighborhood, away from the bustle yet close to restaurants / bars and a stone's throw from the famous Condesa parks.
The house is spacious and bright, with a lovely functional kitchen (w/breakfast table) and a cool living room, both connecting with a beautiful patio yard surrounded by plants, ideal for disconnecting. There's an elegant dining room, two confortable bedrooms and two full art decó bathrooms.

The space
We love living in this house, and only rent it when we're away on vacation. Thus, we try to make it as enjoyable as possible.
To quote some of our past guests, "an absolute gem of a home!, the architecture is breathtaking and the decor is perfect", "it was even more than expected", "the apartment was big and had everything we needed, the patio in the backyard was fantastic for breakfast and to just relax in the afternoon", "great location".
host_about: We're a multicultural couple based in Mexico City who love nature. We really enjoy travelling, visiting new places to meet people, other cultures, and experience new food.

name: RANCHO GUADALUPE  Ajusco Riding Holidays
description:
We have 3 bedrooms for two guests each and a suite with a private Jacuzzi. The Suite can be accommodated for4 persons; it is perfect for small groups and families. This suite has a large King-Size bed and a comfortable bunk bed. All the bedrooms have their own bathroom.
Your stay includes all meals, quality beverages in an open bar and all the riding, of course.

The space
Rancho Guadalupe is an ideal destination for horseback trail riding with beautiful horses and superior, all-inclusive, lodging in a real Mexican Ranch.

Guest access
There is a heated swimming pool, steam sauna, Jacuzzi, squash, tennis and mini basketball court, riding paddock, bar area and lots more...

Other things to note
We are kid friendly. We have a playground, trampoline, Rowing Boats for the pond, petting zoo, badminton and variety games for your little ones.
host_about:
Hey! 
We enjoy Mexico and the lifestyle the ranch allows us. 
We have been passionate about horseback trail riding for many years and now we want to open the door for riders worldwide.

name: Beautiful Art Deco house + Terrace
description:
The house is an example of the beautiful Art Deco architecture of Colonia Roma. It´s located in a private courtyard, so the tranquility and the silence is guarantee during your stay. At the same time, the perfect location, steps away from parks and restaurants, allows all visitors to enjoy the famous cultural live of the neighborhood. It´s the best acommodation for a couple or a family.

The space

name: Beautiful, spacious house in historic Coyoacan
description:
My home is a stunning spacious house on one of Mexico City's most historic streets. It is filled with exquisite art work and very close to the center of colonial Coyoacán. A supermarket and beautiful park are nearby. It is a fairly close to the UNAM and is a great home to rent by week or month.

The house has 2 bedrooms with private bathrooms and walk-in closets. The upstairs bedroom has folding shutters for more or less privacy.

There is also a Swedish style sauna for the cold winter nights!

The space
The outside patio is full of plants and is the perfect place to sit in the sun and enjoy a morning or afternoon coffee or tea. It is shared with a small studio apartment.

When you step outside the house you are on one of Mexico City's most beautiful streets where you can find people strolling at all hours of the day. A short 15 to 20-minute walk will take you to the center of Coyoacan, to the famous Frida Kahlo Museum, or to one of t
host_about: I was born in L.A. but moved to Mexico City as a young girl. I grew up speaking and writing both English and Spanish and feel at home in both countries. I have lived in Playa del Carmen for the past 18 years and have watched it grow and transform. It's been a trip!

La Condesa is one of Mexico City's fashionable neighborhoods, with designer shops and beautiful parks. La Condesa’s cosmopolitan vibe attracts the likes of artists, intellectuals and business people who bring their individual styles to the scene. This place recalls the Palermo neighborhood in Buenos Aires or SOHO in New York.

One of the appeals of Condesa is simply the beauty of it’s streets. It’s made up of lots of charming, wide avenues, with trees that form a canopy above. When you’re in one of the biggest cities in the world, these touches of nature are greatly appreciated.

El barrio es uno de los más tradicionales y antiguos de la ciudad, con grandes casas y un parque central con un kiosco realmente especial, aquí aún se conserva el sabor mexicano pero teniendo todos los servicios a la mano, la calle donde se encuentra la casa tiene tiendas de abarrotes, verdulería y frutería, tortillería, lavandería, panadería, estética, todos atendidos por vecinos lo cuál lo hace más interesante, aquí tendrás todo para tener un estancia confortable.

Alrededor del parque y en la colonia en general encontrarás comida de todo tipo como oaxaqueña, yucateca, rusa, china, japonesa y un gran número de cafés para pasar un buen rato, puedes también comer y tomar una cerveza en la cantina llamada "Salón Paris" que está en una esquina del parque y que es una de las más tradicionales.

A sólo dos cuadras de la casa encontrarás un gran centro comercial con tiendas, cine, bancos, restaurantes etc.

neiborhood_overview:
The colonia Romahas been an exclusive area for the wealthy on the edge of the city when it was built in the very early 20th century.

It has a Bohemian area with restaurants, art galleries, offices and more. Today, the area attracts younger generations of artists, writers and urban hipsters. Most of the streets are quiet and lined with large, leafy trees, mostly how they were laid out when the colonia was built.

The largest street is Avenida Álvaro Obregón, whose traffic islands have large trees, walking paths and metal benches. On weekends, these islands fill with vendors selling art, antiques and collectibles. long with the tree lined streets, green spaces were also created with the addition of small parks called plazas.

Other things to note
La colonia es excelente

El departamento está dividido en dos pisos. En el primer piso se encuentra el área social con Bar, Recibidor, Sala, Comedor, Cocina, 2 medios baños, alacena y cuarto de lavado. En la parte superior se encuentra el Estudio, 2 Baños Completos, Recámara Principal y dos Recámaras Secundarias.

The space
El departamento cuenta con sistema inteligente y automatizado de luces, persianas y sonido. Limpieza diaria incluida (lunes a sábado).

Guest access
Todo el departamento es exclusivamente para la persona que lo rente. No comparte ningún área con los vecinos

La zona es muy conocida por la gran cantidad de cafés, librerías, restaurantes, galerías y boutiques, así como por su vida cultural y nocturna. La Condesa comparte su frontera y espíritu bohemio con la Colonia Roma, y juntas forman el llamado Corredor Cultural Roma Condesa. Una de las principales características actuales de la colonia Condesa es la juventud de sus colonos, lo que le proporciona un aire cosmopolita, representado de forma más visible por su vida nocturna y gastronómica, un estilo de vida desenfadado, donde las bicicletas retro y la compañía de los perros como mascotas salpican sus calles y pegatina alternativa. Asimismo, es común la filmación de películas, comerciales o programas de televisión en las calles.

The house is designed with our guests in mind, so you will find everything you need such as blender, kettle, coffee maker, stove, microwave, iron, ironing board, a large dinning table and TV with Netflix.

La casa es muy grande! Hay 4 habitaciones y 4 baños completos, una cocina estilo americano, sala y barra de café.

name: Casa Alquimia @ Desierto de los Leones
description:
Alquimia: Casa de los elementos.

Este mágico lugar en el maravilloso bosque del Desierto de los Leones es una casa con 25 años de historia pero recientemente remodelada y adaptada para la comodidad de nuestros huéspedes haciendo énfasis en la ciencia mística de la alquimia.

La propiedad esta rodeada de 2,300 m2 de hermosa vegetación y tranquilidad donde podrás percibir directamente la vida y energía del bosque.

The space
Alquimia se encuentra en el corazón del Desierto de los Leones a solo 2 minutos de la carretera principal y cuenta con 4 habitaciones, 4.5 baños y una capacidad para recibir hasta 12 huéspedes.

También cuenta con:
-Estacionamiento privado para 4 autos
-2 diferentes accesos al bosque
-Chimenea de leña
-Una torre externa de cuento de hadas
-Calefacción
-Hermosos jardines al rededor de toda la casa
-Comedor
-Cocina totalmente equipada
-Recibidor
-TVs en todas las hab

host_about:
I was born and raised in Canada and I have been living the past 14 years happily in Mexico City. I work in the education field as well as construction, and while living in the hustle and bustle of the city, it is always nice to get away from it all and head to the outdoors. My family and I love having outdoor activities so accessible to us, and when we are not out adventuring we are close to the grill.

name: La casa del fresno.
description:
This charming house in the heart of historic Coyoacán is a short walk from the main square, the metro and the Frida Kahlo and Trotsky Museums. Feel like going for a walk or a jog? A wooded area called the Viveros de Coyoacan is just a block away. There is no place like Coyoacán to get the true Mexican experience. And this small house, nestled at the back of a lovely garden, offers a serene, well lit oasis for families, groups and business travellers.

The space
Featured in the book Best of the Best: Mexican Architectures 2001 – 2010, this two-storeyed minimalist house is tucked away in the back of a garden and boasts an oak tree in its inner patio. Its stone and wooden floors, white walls and modern wooden cabinetry all add to create a beautiful, organic and tranquil space. host_about:
MyPlace Leisure Homes

¡MI CASA ES TU CASA!

When you stay in one of our properties, you´ll get to experience our history, culture and people with an immersive feel of our traditions all with a touch of design to immerse yourself in our culture. Whether a “lucha libre” decored flat in Centro Histórico, an ultra luxury condo in Acapulco, or a restored colonial house, we handpick every one of our homes to give them a unique charm and character and all of them with modern, first-rate amenities and handcrafted local comforts so you can truly relax when visiting Mexico.

With concierge services, hotel amenities, and you can truly relax and live just like you’re at home, but better..

As a hosts, we focus on the little details so you can have the best stay possible. 

As a guest, I know what hosts go through and feel like, so I'm very respectful of the places I rent. 
As a person.. I love my wife and son!! I have a little dog called Carola (which is a mini xoloizcuintle). I love to travel and consider myself a foodie.

Coyoacán es uno de los barrios más bonitos e interesantes de la ciudad. Su arquitectura conserva vestigios de un México; ha sido habitado por personajes muy importantes dentro de la cultura mexicana desde entonces: pintores, intelectuales, escritores, poetas, historiadores, cineastas, músicos, artesanos, actores, escenógrafos, bailarines, grabadores, escultores etcétera, por lo que se considera un barrio cultural por excelencia.

Coyoacan is a beautiful and interesting neighborhood; his architecture preserves an old Mexico and is a place full of history and arts because has been inhabited for huge personalities from Mexican culture, painters, intellectuals, writers, poets, historians, filmmakers musicians craftsmen, actors, sculptors, teachers, dancers etc. Is a cultural neighborhood for excellence.

description:
Un espacio ideal si vienes al sur de la CDMX, caminando a zona de hospitales (Gea, cardiología, cancerología, nutrición, Iner, psiquiatría) en mb a 3 est de neurología, 10 min del INR Y Estadio Azteca, caminando al Centro de Tlalpan; un lugar colonial con Iglesias, mercados, restaurantes, bares, imperdible comer el caldo tlalpeño, a 15 min de Six Flags y Xochimilco, 5 mins del parque Loreto y Peña pobre. Muy cerca del Ajusco, bosque de Tlalpan, en la salida a Cuernavaca, ideal para fin de sem.

The space
Un espacio sencillo y creativo.
Súper tranquilo para crear, pensar o pasar una noche romántica.
Ambientes amplios con iluminación creativa. Está en un primer piso y tiene lugar de estacionamiento privado en frente del depto.
El lugar ideal para alejarte del ajetreo de la ciudad sin salirte de ella!
El departamento cuenta con una oficina equipada en caso de venir por trabajo. Jardín común.

name: Mama Mia house in beautiful “Roma” long-term only
description:
Casa SIN AMUEBLAR 125mts2

- 2 recámaras
- 1 Alcoba
- 1 patio (privado)
- 2 baños completos
- Sala y comedor
- Cocina integral
- Cuarto de lavado
- Terraza (Privada) 70 mts2
- Area de almacenamiento
- 1 lugar de estacionamiento
- tanque estacionario
- Cisterna + 3 Tinacos, capacidad total 8,000 ltrs de almacenamiento.

Es la casa inferior de una casa duplex, con entrada independiente, ubicada en una zona hipster muy de moda, Roma Norte, insuperable ubicación, con fáciles vías de acceso.

The space
La renta de la casa es únicamente para contratos de 6 meses en adelante Cuenta con todos los servicios y está ubicada en una de las mejores zonas de la ciudad, es parte de un condominio horizontal y se renta SIN AMUEBLAR

El patio te permite disfrutar de tu café por la mañana o una rica velada por la tarde. La azotea tiene vista al castillo de Chapultepec donde puedes tomar el sol, lee
host_about:
Hola! Gracias por revisar mi perfil. 

Cuento con dos habitaciones en renta. Tengo una casa en planta baja (de casa duplex)  Ciudad de México, excelentemente bien ubicada. A 5 km de centro historico, a 2 cuadras del Bosque de Chapultepec, a 1 cuadra del metro Chapultepec, a 5 del Parque España y a 2 de Avenida Reforma.

 Ubicada en la colonia Roma Norte, una zona muy hipster, con mucha seguridad y vías de comunicación a todas partes.

 Me gusta viajar y conozco las necesidades de viajero, tales como llegar a un lugar limpio y seguro, encontrar información de utilidad y que me brinde un espacio para sentirme en casa.

Un poco de mí: Actualmente, soy activista en temas de derechos de los animales, desarrollo urbano y asistencia a personas de la tercera edad. También, soy consultor en negocios y desarrollo social. 

Estudié un Bachelor’s en negocios internacionales, en Texas, USA, cuento con dos diplomados en el área y una maestría.

Con la idea de disfrutar un poco más de la vida y de los frutos de una vida de trabajo. Quisiera ahora poder compartir mi espacio aquí en casa (yo vivo aquí), con personas respetuosas, limpias y honestas a quienes como a mí les guste viajar, vivir y compartir nuevas experiencias.

 Espero poder asistir y ser parte de una grata experiencia en la Ciudad de México. Gracias

neiborhood_overview:
La Roma Norte es una zona Hipster, llena de galerías y restaurantes. Es una mezcla perfecta entre habitaciones residenciales, oficinas y comercios. Muy céntrico. A una cuadra del metro y central de camiones para cualquier punto de la ciudad. Con mucha vigilancia y seguridad. A calles de una de las zonas mas populares en cuanto a restaurantes y vida nocturna, bares etc. A dos cuadras del Centro Financiero, a dos cuadras de Reforma, una de las avenidas principales. A dos cuadras del Bosque de Chapultepec y a 10 minutos de caminata a los museos de Antropología, Tamayo y Arte Moderno.
Algunas características de los habitantes de la Roma Norte/Condesa son son animal lovers, eco-friendly, tipo new age. Una zona muy codiciada donde también habitan muchos extranjeros.

name: Bueno, bonito, barato y céntrico! Siglo XXI
description:
La habitación más pequeña que tenemos (pero súper cómoday con roof garden)! Es ideal para el viajero con poco equipaje, cuenta con una cama individual perfecta para después de un largo viaje. Esta acondicionada con una pequeña mesa y cuenta con un baño compartido (Max. 1 persona).

Por la cómoda y céntrica ubicación no tendrás ningún inconveniente para llegar a ninguna parte de la CDMX.

Está pensada para llegar y dormir cómodamente. Además tendrás una gran vista desde el roof garden!

The space
Es una habitación pequeña con una litera, sillón abajo y cama arriba. Pensada para recibir a viajeros con poco equipaje, que busquen tranquilidad a un buen precio. No es

Guest access
Escaleras y roof garden.

Other things to note
Ojo con el check in y el check out, revísalo antes de reservar ya que está programado a partir de las 8 pm. De ser posible podemos recibirte antes pero debemos checar disponibilida
host_about:
Soy una persona joven y alegre, con muchas ganas de conocer gente nueva y transmitirles mi amor por la CDMX. Mi esposa Erandi y yo les queremos invitar a nuestro hogar donde seguro tendrán una experiencia increíble y conocerán el estilo de vida dinámico de los capitalinos, además de disfrutar de la tranquilidad y calidez en nuestra casa.

Soy apasionado de casi todo tipo de música, me encanta tocar la guitarra, cocinar, jugar videojuegos, salir a pasear, jugar frontenis, entre otras cosas. 

¡Permitan que hagamos de su estancia en la CDMX, la mejor! ¡Los esperamos!

name: CASA/SUR/COAPA/CDMX/FAMILY/HOSPITALES/UNAM/TEC.
description:
"Villa del Sur" Es el lugar perfecto para unas vacaciones, citas médicas o viajes de negocios.
Tan pronto entres a la casa, te sentirás acogido en un agradable lugar privado y muy bien equipado que llenará tu día a día de confort.
Lo mejor de esta casa, además de que su increíble ubicación te permitirá desplazarte por toda la Ciudad de México, es que está hecha y remodelada para tí que estás leyendo y que no sabes dónde alojarte en la CDMX.

The space
"Villa del Sur" es un espacio que te brindará privacidad, confort y practicidad sobrepasando tus expectativas. Este alojamiento fue diseñado para los intrepidos viajeros que buscan divertirse, para las familias que dan largos paseos o las parejas que buscan privacidad. No busques más, en "Villa del Sur" te garantizamos una estancia mágica.
También está diseñada para los que desean descansar y reponerse de una cita o tratamiento médico. Te garantizamos un lugar acogedor, como si estuvieras en casa.

neiborhood_overview:
"Villa del Sur" se encuentra en el corazón de "Coapa" una zona de la ciudad de México con gran renombre, conocida por su vida nocturna, sus parques y la cordialidad de sus habitantes.
Está rodeada de plazas comerciales nuevas como son "Galerías Coapa" "Gran Terraza Coapa" y "Paseo Acoxpa". Es una zona con muchos negocios que te harán difícil la tarea de escoger dónde comer o dónde tomar un trago.
Hay vigilancia las 24 hrs y la zona cuenta con alarmas de emergencia y cámaras de seguridad.
Podrás desplazarte fácilmente a diferentes zonas de interés como las famosas Trajineras de Xochimilco, San Ángel, Coyoacán o el Centro Histórico de la ciudad de México.
También está cerca de diferentes Hospitales de especialidades, por si visitas la ciudad por cuestiones médicas.

neiborhood_overview:
Founded in 1906, La Roma is characterized by Parisian Style boulevards and highly eclectic architecture, with various art nouveau styles, ranging from the late 19th to early 20th century.

But la Roma is not only for architecture enthusiasts, food lovers be aware that just two blocks away from Roma Spot, on Álvaro Obregón Street, you can grab a bite in one of the dozens of award winning five star restaurants, or just wonder around and get a taste of the local street cuisine, and yes, by that we mean things like all kinds of taco’s imaginable to the human mind!!!

Other things to catch in La Roma/Condesa area that will surely tickle your explorer bug include: coffee shop’s, art galleries, parks, yoga and wellness centers, antiques stores, vintage bookstores, art cinema’s, museums, barber shops, cultural and spiritual hubs, local artisan shops and some of the best fashion boutiques from up and coming international designers that you won’t find anywhere else in Mexic

Soy maestra en pedagogía del arte, me gusta viajar por el mundo dos veces al año y he descubierto que todos lo podemos hacer, sobre todo por este medio.
Ofrezco mi casa en Morelos y un departamento en Mexico df cerca del estadio azteca, para visitar mi país que es increíble.

name: La casa del Jardín
description:
La ubicación de esta casa es una de las mejores que se encuentra en el centro histórico de Coyoacán, donde podrá explorar todas las zonas y sentirse como una persona de este barrio.

The space
Hospedarse en nuestra casa hará que disfrute un hogar con arquitectura colonial y contrastada con diseños actuales, por las mañanas podrá disfrutar con toda tranquilidad un jardín que lo hará sentir relajado, disfrutando de las plantas a su alrededor.
Podrá usted también a pocos metros, disfrutar de restaurantes, cervecerías y bares, así como centros culturales, librerías, galerías y otros.
Podrá usted disfrutar de nuestra terraza para relajarse y si gusta podrá hacer uso del asador con unos ricos cortes o cocina de su autoría.
Para los momentos de gozar el interior de la casa contamos con información de restaurantes con servicio a domicilio quienes cuentan con variedad de cocina la cual usted podrá pedir por cualquier medio de entregas.

description:
Esta es nuestra casa pero cuando no estamos en la ciudad la compartimos con otras personas. Para nosotros es un oasis en plena ciudad, en un barrio tranquilo y silencioso. En el jardín hay un huerto donde puedes cosechar hierbas aromáticas o verduras según la estación. Es un lugar muy relajado con espacio al aire libre y perfecto para personas que buscan, no un hotel sino un hogar con jardín.

Usamos jabón de cuerpo y manos líquido que es biodegradable y sin envases. Hacemos composta y tenemos un huerto orgánico que puedes cuidar o bien solo cosechar.

El barrio es muy tranquilo, puedes caminar y disfrutar de su tranquilidad. El centro histórico de coyoacán y la zona con museos está a 15 minutos en automóvil. En la colonia puedes encontrar la tienda Zero Market (de filosofía Zero Waste), pastelería y pan Marce y café en Blessed coffee. Puedes comprar frutas y verduras al mercado al final de la cuadra o en el tianguis los días miércoles a 3 cuadras de la casa.
Para comer cerca te recomiendo:
Pozole de Guerrero a 3 cuadras (Manjar del sur), Sushi rico a 3 cuadras (Sushi Hana), Quesadillas y flautas a 4 cuadras (Las Quekas Factory), aguachiles y mariscos estilo Sonora a 6 cuadras (Puro Sinaloa) y tacos deliciosos (Los Chavos), Cemitas y tortas a 8 cuadras (Cemitas y tortas la estrella). O puedes comer en el tianguis unos ricos tlacoyos, quesadillas, tacos de mixiote o barbacoa los días miércoles (Av 6 in front of Montessori Laurel).
**Busca el nombre en GooglxMaps**

host_about:
Hola!  Gusto en conocerte. Soy Gaby Madrid.
Será un placer poderte hospedar.
Me gusta recomendar lugares que visitar en la Ciudad de México, es una Ciudad Hermosa, que ofrece lugares increíbles para todos, ya sea que viajes con la familia, con amigos, o de trabajo, para descansar, de vacaciones o por conocer una Ciudad que de verdad te encantará.
Hay muchos lugares que conocer: el Centro de la Ciudad, museos, restaurantes, bares, cafés, centros comerciales, plazas, parques, lugares donde la gente local comemos y disfrutamos de un buen café. Estaré disponible para recomendarte lugares si así lo deseas. 
Nuestro principal objetivo es ofrecer estancias en lugares tranquilos, seguros, muy bien ubicados, cerca de los lugares más importantes de la Ciudad.
Como huésped siempre busco lugares céntricos donde hospedarme, restaurantes que me ofrezcan comida típica, a buen precio, donde pueda hacer una sobremesa agradable.
Como anfitrión me gusta recomendar lugares, preguntanos a tu llegada y con gusto te recomendaremos lugares que visitar.
Bienvenidos a la Ciudad de México CDMX!

Hello! Nice to meet you, I am Gaby Madrid. 
I love to recommend places of Mexico City. It is a big city that offers many places for everybody: very good food, a lot of places to drink something and enjoy the days with your family and friends, cultural places, trendy places, shopping, walking, coffees, fun, etc. 
You will love Mexico City too.
Our main priority is to offer to all of our guests places with great location in Mexico City, safe and quiet places, in order to let you enjoy the City and to get a very pleasant stay.
Me, as guest, I always choose safe places, good located: in known neighborhoods of the cities, excellent hosts, places that allows me to walk around, to eat very well in special places: local places, not so expensive, but the most important: tasty and excellent local food, I like to know the most important places, and hoping to love the place, so I will surely travel there again.
As host, I will welcome you and could recommend places to visit in Mexico City when you arrive if you like to.
About our places: Please check the dates, if some of them is booked, we have more places in very good neighborhoods as well, please ask me, it will be a pleasure to receive you.
Welcome to Mexico City!

name: Bella casa para grupos, en el corazón de Coyoacan.
description:
La casa se encuentra solamente a 3 calles de uno de los principales centros culturales del país, el mítico Jardín Hidalgo, centro de Coyoacán espacio lleno de cafés, bares, exquisitos restaurantes y demás.

La casa corona una hermosa privada, la cuál cuenta con seguridad las 24 horas, y tendrás acceso a diversos ambientes con una atmósfera tranquila y placentera; cocina, sala, comedor, asador y una espectacular terraza; totalmente equipada, lista para hacerte pasar una estancia inolvidable.

The space
Espectacular casa, bellamente decorada, iluminada y con vistas a un bello jardín, lo que la la posibilidad de entrar en una atmósfera de relajación y disfrutar del bello barrio de Coyoacán.
La casa es de una hermosa arquitectura moderna, contrastada con bellos detalles tradicionales, que enaltecen la belleza de nuestra Mexicanidad. La delicada combinación entre lo tradicional y lo moderno, son acompañados por diversas obras de arte de artistas locale
host_about:
Soy sociólogo de profesión y ayudante de investigador en UNAM, y mi esposa es pedagoga. Somos grandes aficionados a viajar y sabemos cuáles son las necesidades de los viajeros, por eso nos volvimos anfitriones, para ofrecer las mejores condiciones para todo aventurero. 

Precisamente por eso, tenemos una cooperativa dedicada a organizar las mejores experiencias en viajes de placer, de incentivo y cualquier tipo de evento empresarial. Danos un vistazo: www. (Website hidden by Airbnb)

neiborhood_overview:
Coyoacán es uno de los espacios con mayor belleza cultural del país, es simplemente único, es como viajar en el tiempo y llegar a un pequeño pueblo, donde la oferta culinaria es inmejorable, los mejores cafés y restaurantes de la ciudad se encuentran aquí. El Mercado de Coyoacán es un espacio lleno de color, y diversidad. Tenemos el mítico Museo Frida Kahlo que convoca a miles de turistas.

Coyoacán tiene más de mil años de historia, el misticismo se respira, aquí vivieron los españoles a su llegada y desde aquí se fraguó la conquista de México al derrotar el Imperio Mexica, la casa de Hernan Cortés actualmente es un delicioso restaurante, aquí se encuentra la capilla más antigua de México, es un espacio repleto de centros culturales, teatros y conciertos.

Coyoacán tiene una esencia mágica, qué nos ha inspirado a acoger visitantes, y compartir con Uds la magia de nuestra casa y de Coyoacán.
neighborhood_overview:
Coyoacán es uno de los espacios con mayor belleza cultural del país, es simplemente único, es como viajar en el tiempo y llegar a un pequeño pueblo, donde la oferta culinaria es inmejorable, los mejores cafés y restaurantes de la ciudad se encuentran aquí. El Mercado de Coyoacán es un espacio lleno de color, y diversidad. Tenemos el mítico Museo Frida Kahlo que convoca a miles de turistas.

Coyoacán tiene más de mil años de historia, el misticismo se respira, aquí vivieron los españoles a su llegada y desde aquí se fraguó la conquista de México al derrotar el Imperio Mexica, la casa de Hernan Cortés actualmente es un delicioso restaurante, aquí se encuentra la capilla más antigua de México, es un espacio repleto de centros culturales, teatros y conciertos.

Nearby it is also possible to find services for all kind of budgets and functions. Due to its privileged location, it connects with the various public transport networks and fast-track arteries.

description:
Casa muy amplia, acogedora y bien iluminada en el sur de la Ciudad de México, con cochera y dos terrazas con bonitas vistas del Ajusco. El hermoso jardín interior abarca los tres niveles y da al ambiente mucha paz! La casa tiene acabados de madera y está decorada con mucho cariño para que te sientas como en tu hogar! Muy, muy cerca de zona de hospitales (Tlalpan), el Estadio Azteca y la UNAM, en un lugar tranquilo y sin ruido.

LUGAR NO APTO PARA FIESTAS O BORRACHERAS.

The space
La habitación principal es enorme, cuenta con vestidor y baño propio. Además de las terrazas, hay un cómodo estudio ideal para desconectar o trabajar. En la cochera caben hasta dos autos (y uno más puede quedarse justo afuera, frente a la fechada, sin ningún problema).

name: Lovely house w/ rooftop in the heart of Condesa
description:
Cute and cosy little house in Condesa. 2 floors with a bedroom&bathroom each plus a little rooftop full of plants and flowers!

The house is located in a private neighborhood in Condesa, that feels like a little colourful village in the heart of the city. It is safe, quiet, & a 10mn walk from Chapultepec park / 2mn from Condesa's bars, restaurants & shops.
It is not a professional Airbnb, humbly our beloved house that we rent when we're not around :) we hope you enjoy it as much as we do!

The space
On the ground floor, you'll enter directly into the bright and stylish living room, and access to the small but cute and functional kitchen.
A large wooden staircase leads to the first bedroom (which is quite big!) and its bathroom.
Then on the first floor is another bright, cute & cosy room and the door to the rooftop full of plants, flowers and with its very own hammoc ;)
The metallic staircase is a little steep (cf pictures), but no pro
host_about:
Axelle & Olivier, 33 years old french couple living in Mexico DF
Axelle is a sculptor who works with ceramics, Oli an engineer passionate about mobility. 
We love travelling, music and cooking  :)

name: Modern Mexican House POLANCO, LARGE GROUPS
description:
Stunning modern, Mexican home in the heart of Polanco!
Perfect for large groups, family vacations and business trips!

The house is spacious, colorful and very comfortable, modern and newly renovated with a traditional Mexican style, fit for 10 people, with 4 rooms, living room, dining room, fully equipped kitchen and a big patio to enjoy sunny days!

Just 2 blocks away from Masaryk, right in the center of Polanco, close by Parque Lincoln, with an unbeatable location!

The space
The space is big, bright and very colorful! The house was recently renovated, and has 4 rooms, each one with a king size bed and it's own bathroom, TV room with a sofa bed, kitchen, dining room, and a beautiful patio!

With a capacity for 10 people to enjoy and be comfortable!

Other things to note
Check in/out out of the established times has a $500 pesos fee
ID required for check in

neiborhood_overview:
The house is located right in the center of Polanco, a few steps from Masaryk, one of the main streets in Mexico City, filled with boutique shops and great restaurants!

Also close by you can reach Parque Lincoln, where you'll be able to find plenty of delicious restaurants.

Polanco is best known for its luxurious shops and restaurants, it's very centric and tranquil, perfect to walk and get to know the city, around you'll be able to find important museums such as Museo de Antropología, Museo Soumaya, Museo Jumex, Museo Tamayo and more!

Very close to important parts of the city such as Condesa/Roma, one of the trendiest areas of the city, Chapultepec, where you can find the stunning park and all that it has to offer, and the city center with it's beautiful and iconic architecture.

Polanco is the best spot to stay and get to know the area and the city!

name: Florida San Angel Coyoacan   Zona segura Mexico
description:
Sencilla-petit, súper impecable! Con aromas suaves y relajantes! Baño independiente bello y todo desinfectado para que te sientas en un espacio agradable! Contamos con estacionamiento al pie de tu habitación! Lo más lindo es la hospitalidad y privacidad que ofrecemos con asesoría gratuita para destinos turísticos o costo adicional de guía. A 5 minutos de Coyoacan, metrobus cercano, muy cerca de San Angel, centrico, libros de lectura, wifi, artículos de tocador, plancha, desayuno y café.

The space
Es petit e impecable!! Contamos con estacionamiento, asesoría a los mejores lugares turísticos y restaurantes:) contamos con guía y recorridos a el turibus de Cdmx. Tenemos pan y café de la mejor calidad hecho por barista- fruta de la estación, wifi, calefacción, aire acondicionado, plancha, libros de lectura, artículos de tocador. Contamos con aroma terapia todo de lavanda toallas y sábanas impecables.

- 5 Minutos museo Frida Kahlo.
-15 Museo Casa estudi
host_about: Soy Jimena, me encanta poder alojar a personas de buena voluntad! Me encanta poder recibir a huéspedes y mi objetivo es que sientan en un ambiente cálido y de paz; soy una persona muy servicial, me agrada la sensación de que todo esté súper limpio los buenos y delicados olores espacios cómodos,cuido cada detalle, me encantan los detalles en telas y en todo:) soy muy sencilla y me gusta lo natural y auténtico;) amo a mi Mexico y me encanta que otros conozcan de mi cultura de los antiguos prehispánicos, me gusta leer la cultura mi pasión es el arte :) mi esposo es fotógrafo y yo también, somos amantes del café hacemos magia con el, le damos una guía de que visitar a nuestros huéspedes y de las atracciones acompañados de un estupendo café y un delicioso pan artesanal o fruta de la estación; con nosotros encontrarán privacidad y calma nunca indiferencia :) espero poder conocer nueva gente y poder ser de ayuda :)

name: Casa en la Roma norte
description:
Casa clásica, en una calle con arquitectura inigualable que te hace sentir totalmente con tranquilidad, la casa cuenta con 7 recámara y las recámaras 1, 2, 3 y 4 tienen baño propio y solo las otras 3 comparten baño pero aparte hay otro medio baño en planta baja y otro en roof garden, la sala comedor está prevista para que pueda ser utilizada para 13 personas y ahí puedes encontrar juegos de mesa para un rato de convivencia.

The space
El espacio es único y la ubicación también si te hospedas aquí tienes que aprovechar que a tan solo 3 cuadras puedes encontrar el Mercado de Medellín donde puedes encontrar desde comida típica mexicana hasta todo lo de centro America cómo comida y productos Colombianos, Venezolanos etc.
A solo 10 min caminando a condesa y al rededor a solo 1 min restaurantes con una de las mejores gastronomías de la cuidad sin duda la colonia roma es un sitio donde nunca te aburrirás ya no solo hay cosas para hacer de día, si no también de noch

name: Cómodo y bien ubicado.
description:
La casa es un lugar en el que se aprecia un ambiente tranquilo rodeado de vegetación. Cada espacio está diseñado y pensado para que el huésped disfrute de la comodidad en sus habitaciones decoradas con toques mexicanos que nos remiten a lo tradicional.
Muy cercana a los centros de espectáculos más importantes y al Centro de la Ciudad de México en una de las colonias más antiguas de la ciudad.
Cuenta con todos los servicios para hacer su estancia placentera.

The space
¡Aceptamos mascotas! Facilitamos implementos como camas o bebederos para mascotas (en caso de que se requiera).
La casa tiene un patio de aproximadamente 4x4m.
A unas calles del Centro comercial Soriana, Vips, restaurantes y establecimientos como papelería, lavandería, panadería, tiendas etc.
Es una colonia muy tranquila y limpia. La casa esta ubicada en la parte trasera de una casa que se usa como oficina, por lo que, en momentos el patio es compartido.

Gue

name: Big, bright and beautiful three story house !
description:
Beautiful 1940's three stories house right in the heart of Mexico City. The ground floor includes a big open space with living, dining, and kitchen area with access to the blue patio leading to the studio and rooftop, which includes a lush bathroom. First floor has two spacious and luminous bedrooms, both with queen beds. Bedroom 1 comes with its own private bathroom. There is a second bathroom on the landing near bedroom 2. The house is very bright, quiet and located in a safe residential area.

The space
The house is at the end of a private alley and located in one of the safest areas of Mexico City. It is well equipped and suitable for both shorter and longer stays, between friends, for business and/or family vacation. The house has several living areas, indoors and outdoors.

Guest access
You have access to the full house, including a private big rooftop

Our unique, cosy, and sunny home comfortably houses 1 to 2 people. We are located in a house behind a house so there is very little street noise. You also have access to our garden, perfect for outdoor brunches or evening drinks! Secluded enough to have privacy and a good rest within this vibrant city. Anyone looking to get fully immersed in Mexico City should definitely stay here. Enjoy all of the comforts of this amazing home!

The space
Tastefully decorated and functional, the house has two floors, each with its own open-air space (front garden and a small terrace), as well as an additional rooftop. An equipped custom kitchen and dining room are on the ground floor. Bedroom, bathroom, living, corridor with floor-to-ceiling windows, a study, shelving, and terrace are on the 1st floor.

name: Casa del Sol
description:
Frente al museo Frida Kahlo.
Casa completa para familias o grupos de hasta 6 personas. Disfruta de una de las zonas más bellasy tradicionales de la Ciudad de México.
La Casa del Sol ubicada en el centro de Coyoacán es el lugar ideal para familias y viajeros de todo el mundo.
Pedimos por favor lean toda la información que proveemos para que sepan lo que ofrecemos. Cualquier duda con gusto les responderemos a la brevedad.

The space
La Casa del Sol
Disfrute de una las zonas más bellas y tradicionales de la Ciudad de México en una casa típica mexicana.
La Casa del Sol es un lugar ideal para familias y viajeros de todo el mundo, cuenta con 3 habitaciones, cocina,sala, comedor, y estudio.
host_about:
Somos una familia de Coyoacán muy amistosa y amable. Mi esposo Jesús es diseñador gráfico y yo soy vendedora. Nos gusta conocer gente y formar nuevas amistades de alrededor del mundo. Disfrutamos mucho de aprender nuevas cosas de otras culturas y tradiciones.
Procuramos mantener un ambiente de paz y armonía. Entendemos que todos los huéspedes son distintos lo que significa siempre distintas experiencias, y nuestra meta es que todos tengan una experiencia maravillosa y aprender y mejorar de cada uno.

neiborhood_overview:
En la Casa del Sol tenemos el privilegio de estar frente a la Casa de la célebre artista Frida Kahlo. Además de que allí está ubicada la para del Turibus Ciudad de México, el cual con un sólo boleto les llevará a recorrer los mejores sitios turísticos de la Ciudad.
Estamos a tan solo 2 cuadras del mercado de Coyoacán y a 4 cuadras del Centro Histórico de Coyoacán. Uno de los lugares más antiguos y tradicionales de toda la ciudad.
Aquí también encontrarán servicios de restaurantes, bares, fuentes de soda, librerías, bibliotecas, el tradicional café "El Jarocho" y el mercado de artesanías, además de museos, entre otras muchas opciones para disfrutar.
