name: Casa Tita Celia: Vintage place to relax
description:
Vintage and cozy house (constructed in the early XX century) in one of the oldest and best located neighborhoods of México City, which will transport you to a pleasant past, where the wide and quiet spaces were (and remain) the most important value to rest and relax. The patio, with a nice fountain, is the ideal place to read, meditate or just relax a little. It is very close to the Alameda de Santa María, Monumento a la Revolution and 10 minutes from Insurgentes Avenue.

The space
**El incumplimiento de cualquiera de las reglas de alojamiento implica cancelación inmediata del servicio**

This beautiful house is perfect for business or vacation, family or single, or just to arrive, leave your things, take a bath and go out immediately to get to know the city.

You will find privacy, tranquility, silence and widespaces throughout the house, which has a patio full of nature where you can take your time to read, rest or write your travel diary acc
host_about:
Soy periodista y escritor. Amante de los viajes, de la naturaleza, de la lectura, del ciclismo y de dar largas caminatas... y como buen viajero, convencido de que conocer personas de diferentes culturas y con diferentes formas de ver la vida es la clave para tender puentes y entrelazar historias. Bienvenidos!

I'm a journalist and writer. Traveler in love with nature, reading, cycling and long walks ... and as a good traveler, convinced that meeting people from different cultures and with different points of view about life is the key to create bridges and interweave stories. Welcome!

name: Centro de Coyoacan Una escapada  con la familia
description:
Casa típica en el Centro de Coyoacan a unos metros del Jardin principal Centenario y 10 min caminando del Museo Frida Kahlo, La Casa cuenta con todos los servicios para sentirse como en casa. Encontraras un plus en cuanto a la comodidad ademas de ser un hogar que cuida el medio ambiente
Es un espacio cálido y familiar y podrás disfrutar una estancia muy agradable, La casa tiene mucha luz natural, la ropa de cama 100% algodón y cuidamos mucho la limpieza para una estancia segura

The space
A tu llegada encontraras un lugar muy acogedor, con cómodos espacios muy iluminados, ventilados y espacioso podrás relajarte y disfrutar de la Ciudad de Mexico.
Los transportes principales están a pie de calle , El metro esta a 5 minutos y El Turibus hace parada a solo 250 metros para recorrer toda la ciudad y después del paseo llegar a casa en una de las zonas más seguras de Coyoacan
La casa tiene una ubicación excelente además una calle tranquila co
host_about:
Mi familia 
Disfruto mucho saber que mis invitados disfruten su estadía en Coyoacan y se sientan, seguros y tranquilos como  en casa ,  esta actividad es muy agradable como trabajo y como pasatiempo. 
Las ventas es mi profesión , me gusta la Historia, cocinar,  disfruto conocer culturas nuevas, diferente idiomas 
Adoro viajar, encontrar restos de la historia, culturas y pueblos es adrenalina para mi. 
compartir  en casa y saber que tuvieron la una agradable estancia en Coyoacán me hace realmente feliz .

name: Private Condesa House with pool in calm street
description:
The house is located in the heart of La Condesa, one of the trendiest and greenest neighborhoods of Mexico City, sets on a calm street, close to everything, but far from noise. The house has three bedrooms all with private bathrooms, a private pool, two separate office rooms to work with two internet lines about 120 mb speed, three private terraces, a living room, a dining area, and a kitchen. You can enjoy the peace, the sunlight, relax in the pool and try our freshly made Mexican breakfast!

The space
The three storey house is located in a calm street in the neighbourhood of La Condesa, creatively renovated and elegantly decorated by the owners.

Guest access
Guests have the whole house on their own.

Other things to note
You will have a freshly made Mexican breakfast from Monday to Saturday between 8-11 AM, made by our housekeeper lady Lydia.

In case of working remotely you can use two separated office room

The Paseo de la Reforma, the most beautiful avenue in all of Mexico City,  is the majestic entrance door that leads to winding streets lined by lavish mansions located in extensive properties with lush vegetation. This neighborhood is home to the financial and diplomatic elite. Most of the European, Asian and Latin American Embassies are located here and it is the preferred choice for entertainment industry personalities,  CEO´s,  CFO´s, Film & Music Industry Celebrities. Lomas de Chapultepec is to Mexico City what Bel Air is to Los Angeles, Key Biscayne to Miami, The Upper Eastside to New York City or Kensignton to London. name: Beautiful 6 bedroom Mario Pani house in CDMX
description:
Beautiful entire house in the heart of Mexico City. Originally finished in 1962 it has been restored and a new house added to complete a six room guest house each with bathroom en suite and complete with copious and cozy communal indoor lounges and outdoor terraces, bar and a sumptuous sculptural dipping pool.

The space
Perfect for a family or a group of friends who want autonomy and communal space. Chefs kitchen for all to use or book a chef to cater for you.
host_about:
Casa Pani is an elegant Guest House situated in the beautiful and peaceful, residential yet central area of Cuauhtémoc. 
Casa Pani is close to museums, restaurants, parks and yet only twenty minutes from the airport. 
Casa Pani sits on a quiet street close to a magnificent mid-century church with a charming park at the end of the street.
Originally a private house designed by celebrated Mexican architect Mario Pani and finished in 1962. The house has been restored and updated, respecting the original materials and identity of Pani. 
In addition to the 1962 house, a 2019 New House has been thoughtfully designed to reflect and honor Mario Pani’s original house. The New House is set on the other side of the existing two outdoor patios and is connected through a covered walkway.
The two houses together offer six private bedrooms each with bathrooms on suite and all with direct access to light and air. 
There are three large connecting reception rooms. 
Two rooftop terraces. Each bedroom has a Dyson air purifier heater and air cooler. On the ground floor there is an indoor-outdoor dipping pool, a bar and a fully equipped stainless steel chef’s kitchen.
Our furnishings have been thoughtfully selected and include classic pieces by both Mexican and international artists and designers.

name: Casa Martha: Best Location & Comfort in La Condesa
description:
Superbly located home in Mexico's trendiest neighborhood—La Condesa—offering premium comfort for a delightful stay.

Enjoy your morning coffee in the private terrace; or prepare an authentic Mexican meal in the super-equipped kitchen. Shop local ingredients in the organic supermarket across the street.

Spacious rooms, recently redone bathrooms, a two-car garage. This stunner offers all the comforts for modern living—including the possibility of a private concierge to cater to your every need.

The space
Originally designed by a young Mexico City architecture studio, Casa Martha tastefully blends the best of modern design with the warm and colorful decor accents that Mexico is known for. Spread over three levels, the property offers fit-for-purpose ambiances that are distinct—as well as functional.
The house benefits from double-pane windows throughout and access to a private balcony on every floor.

Upon climbing the first set
host_about: I love traveling, food, nature and sports. I am a designer that works across media and value curiosity, inquiry, learning, experimentation, collaboration, cross-functionality, sustainability, inclusion, and respect in the workspace and life. I am a mother of two kids and a wife. We enjoy swimming and hiking together.

Located in the legendary Callejon del Aguacate, this charming house sits in the heart of Coyoacan, one of the most beautiful neighbourhoods in Mexico City.
The house is just a few minute walk from downtown Coyoacan, where you have a a number of delicious restaurants to choose from, local markets, and historic sites to visit.
It's also a walking distance from los Viveros, a huge park where local residents go for a jog, stroll, meditation, karate among other recreational activities.

To note is that Coyoacan is surrounded by a great variety of trees, plants, and flowers which some people might be allergic to. Although very beautiful, in the winter months all this vegetation can make the house pretty chilly.

The kitchen is very spacious and comes fully-equipped. Help yourself to the spices as well.

From here you're just a few blocks from Parque México, cafés, bars, restaurants and supermarkets.

Bike-sharing stations and great tacos are just around the corner.

The space

The bedroom is spacious and has plenty of closet-space for your belongings. It also has direct access to the private bathroom.

If you enjoy cooking, the kitchen has a large countertop and comes with everything you need (common appliances, kitchen utensils, spices and tupperware).

name: Casa Lila Coyoacan: Perfect 3BR & Garden
description:
Disfruta de la paz, la comodidad y el gran espacio de esta hermosa casa en Coyoacán.
La zona está llena de cultura e historia para los amantes del arte y de las experiencias genuinas.

De estilo clásico y con toques de modernidad, la casa se ubica en un área de museos a escasas calles del Museo Frida Kahlo y del mercado de Coyoacán. El Zócalo está a diez minutos en un pintoresco paseo en el que encontrarás exquisita comida mexicana, barecitos y tiendas de artesanías de la región.

The space
Pensada para la comodidad y el descanso después de un día de paseo por los alrededores, en un área privilegiada para disfrutar del silencio y de noches placenteras.
Cada habitación cuenta con amenidades diferentes como jacuzzi, TV con cable, caja de seguridad. La casa cuenta con un hermoso jardín, una sala comedor y cocineta para uso de nuestros invitados.

Con una excelente iluminación, también cuenta con un escritorio para trabajar y leer cóm
host_about:
Soy host de espacios únicos, en excelente ubicación, perfectamente ambientados y equipados con todo lo necesario para ofrecer una estancia placentera e inolvidable. Me encanta el contacto con la gente y ayudarlos a conocer mi ciudad... Llevo años en el servicio de hospitalidad y me encanta mi trabajo pues ni siquiera me parece trabajo. 
Otras actividades que me gusta disfrutar es proporcionar experiencias especiales adicionales a nuestros invitados pues lo veo como un pasatiempo, el ejercicio al aire libre, pasear a mi perro y seguir conociendo mi hermosa ciudad.

name: Selina Mexico City-Small Room Sh Bathroom w/o View
description:
Deep in the heart of downtown Mexico City, Selina is surrounded by beauty and wonder. We’re only a few minutes walk to major landmarks and you can catch glimpses of Aztec ruins from your bedroom.
Selina Mexico City offers a comfortable, relaxing venue. Chill out with our daily yoga classes and take in the breathtaking views of the city from our cozy rooftop bar.

The space
Our downtown Mexico City coworking space has it all. Entrepreneurs and companies will find the perfect environment for learning new skills, productive working, and global networking.
host_about: Selina no es solo alojamiento. En efecto, ofrecemos lugares (bellos, hermosamente diseñados) para alojarse. Pero más que eso, ofrecemos un lugar para conectar con los demás. Déjate inspirar por playas magníficas y selvas exuberantes. Alimenta tu creatividad en centros urbanos llenos de energía. Súbete a una ola, baila hasta el amanecer o alcanza un nuevo nivel de productividad con el surf, actividades, coworking y la comunidad de Selina. Si buscas una experiencia única, de inmersión, llena de propósito, estás buscando Selina.

name: Myplace Leisure Home @ Donceles - 3 Nights #1
description:
A recently renovated historic building with a relaxing roof garden equipped with a grill, a gym, a laundry room, and a lot of charm.

Fully equipped bedroom loft with one queen bed and a very functional sofa bed that transforms either in two twins or one queen-size bed. TV with Netflix and Sat Tv, Bluetooth speaker with CD and AM and FM radio, a well-equipped kitchen and dining table, high-speed internet 30 Mbps, a big safe that can fit your laptop and access to the buildings common areas such as the gym, the terrace, the grill and the laundry room with a washer and a dryer.

Enjoy Mexico City from within the core location of the most amazing and important cultural, traditional touristic places. While you rest in a kind one-bedroom apartment in a newly refurbished old Downtown classic building located at the corner of Donceles and Cajon del 54, just behind the National Art Museum and only one block away from Bellas Artes.

description:
hermosa casa que se encuentra en una zona muy típica con tipoligia de art deco. La casa se encuentra en dos niveles. Subiendo al primer nivel cuenta con sala comedor, cocina, lavandería y una primera recamara, Subiendo la escalera tipo colonial (espiral sin pasamanos) se encuentran la otras 3 recamaras con 3 baños, la recamara principal cuenta con una sala interior tipo suite y una terraza privada.
entre las habitaciones también tiene una sala de convivencia con televisor.
reamente cómoda.

The space
Es una Hermosa casa de la época que cuenta con espacio amplios como sala, comedor, cocina, lavandería, 4 habitaciones y 3 baños, etc

Guest access
para ingresar a la propiedad es necesario subir un primer nivel donde encontrarán las zonas sociales privadas y una recamara, en el siguiente nivel pasando la escalera de espital o avinico se encuentran las otras 3 recamaras

Other things to note
Esta propiedad ocu
host_about:
Soy amante de las artes, admirador de grandeza de los pequeños detalles, de profesión arquitecto. Me encanta viajar y conocer gente nueva, entender hasta donde pueda. Involucrarme en experiencias, retos y metas, aunque todo esto suena muy tirado a ser idealista, disfruto tanto una cerveza fría como un buen vinos, un pan dulce, los amigos y la familia. 
Me encanta compartir experiencias y me encanta escuchar la de otros, soy el típico que platica con el de enfrente de la fila y el de atrás. Tenemos mucho que aprender y mucho que disfrutar.

name: Espectacular Casa en el Corazón de Coyoacán.
description:

La zona está llena de restaurantes y es ideal tanto para el viajero de negocios como el de placer.
Casa El Ángel has an unbeatable location! We are only a few meters away from El Angel de la Independencia and Reforma Av., the most iconic location in the city! We are on a quiet street in the financial district, very close to many restaurants and bars.

The space
Huge house in a great location! There are 4 bedrooms, 4 bathrooms a very large kitchen, living room and coffee bar.
The house is designed with our guests in mind, so you will find everything you need such as blender, toaster, kettle, coffee maker, oven, microwave, iron, ironing board, a large dinning table and TV with Netflix.

La casa es muy grande! Hay 4 habitaciones y 4 baños completos, una cocina estilo americano, sala y barra de café.

name: Acorazadas de Azcapotzalco
description:
Las Acorazadas, abre sus puertas para recibirlos en el corazón de la antigua ciudad de Azcapotzalco uno de los más antiguos de la Ciudad de México, donde han sucedido varios episodios importantes en la historia México. Ideal para residencias artísticas.

The space
Es una casa de principios del siglo XIX ubicada en el centro histórico de Aztcapozalco, área comercial y de interés histórico al noroeste de la CDMX conformado por barrios con orígenes precolombinos y coloniales. El área que ofrecemos es la primera ala de la casa que tiene dos amplias y cómodas habitaciones. Cuenta con cocina abierta, comedor y amplia estancia, el ambiente es muy tranquilo ideal y propicio para crear. Hay un jardín central con árboles frutales donde habitan algunas ardillas y gatos.

Other things to note
La casa está cerca dentro de un área comercial donde hay tiendas, bancos, restaurantes, farmacias, etcétera.

host_about:
Hola!!

Tengo 39 años, me encanta viajar y conocer gente de otras culturas y otras costumbres, aprender otros idiomas, comer cosas distintas. Mi primer acercamiento con Airbnb fue en un viaje alrededor de USA y Canadá. La experiencia fue tan buena que regresando me apunté como host!

Compartí mis otras recámaras en mi casa de Qro durante 3 años. Ahora vivo en el DF y rentó mi depa cuando estoy de viaje, lo cual pasa mucho muy seguido, y uso la aplicación como huésped. 

Soy madre de mi perrija Frida, una scotch terrier de 12 años, sumamente educada y tranquila que siempre anda conmigo.

Airbnb me parece una manera increíble de conocer gente y quien sabe, a la mejor hasta hacer un par de amigos nuevos.

Me gusta mucho ir al cine, leer novelas ya que para mi la lectura es para distraerme, para divertirme y para soñar. Me gusta cocinar, soy ordenada y limpia y una adicta a Netflix :)

neiborhood_overview:
"La Condesa" neighborhood is the home of the artistic upper class and is now a super-young, super-stylish neighborhood that's home to some of the city's best food, drink, art, and parks.
Condesa had great architectural bones from its affluent past, a blend of Art Deco mansions and expansive parks. Today, the more laid-back Condesa is known as a haven for dog lovers (yes, really) and young business types, while the edgier Condesa is where you’ll find third-wave coffee shops and pricey hipster boutiques. Condesa neighborhood is equivalent to Soho in NYC or Shoreditch in London.

La Condesa’s cosmopolitan vibe attracts the likes of artists, students, intellectuals and younger business people who bring their individual styles to the scene.

neiborhood_overview:
"La Roma" neighborhood is the home of the artistic upper class and is now a super-young, super-stylish neighborhood that's home to some of the city's best food, drink, art, and parks.
Condesa and Roma had great architectural bones from its affluent past, a blend of Art Deco mansions and expansive parks. Today, the more laid-back Condesa is known as a haven for dog lovers (yes, really) and young business types, while the edgier Condesa is where you’ll find third-wave coffee shops and pricey hipster boutiques. Condesa neighborhood is equivalent to Soho in NYC or Shoreditch in London.

La Roma’s cosmopolitan vibe attracts the likes of artists, students, intellectuals and younger business people who bring their individual styles to the scene.

Guest access

host_about:
Hola, soy Omar...
Arquitecto de profesión y muchos años dedicado al diseño industrial, primordialmente enfocado a la fabricación de mobiliario, aunque también realizado proyectos de muy diversa índole.
Apasionado del ciclismo y activo precursor de temas relacionados con una cultura de cuidado al medio ambiente (para preservar el único mundo que tenemos).
He sido afortunado de tener contacto con gente de todos lados desde hace mucho tiempo, lo que me ha permitido crear un espectro muy amplio sobre la enorme diversidad y de esa manera facilitar nuevas relaciones.

Nuestra Casa es Iluminada, Ventilada, Cálida , Confortable, Limpia y Ordenada.

Estamos a 15 minutos de Reforma, a 10 de Garibaldi, a 3 de la Basílica de Guadalupe, a 20 de Chapultepec, a 50 de Xochimilco, a 50 de Coyoacán y a 15 de Polanco.

Guest access

Nuestra Casa es LIBRE DE HUMO y NO se permite fum

name: Rosa Chilango
description:
Relájate como un auténtico chilango en esta casa completa, amplia y serena, a unas cuadras del centro de Coyoacán y del centro comercial.

The space
Rosa Chilango es una casa de dos plantas, con tres habitaciones en la parte de arriba, y en la de abajo, una amplia sala, comedor para ocho personas, sala de juegos, estudio y cocina. Tiene un espacio de estacionamiento en el patio.

Está súper bien ubicada en el sur de la Ciudad de México, en Coyoacán. Podrás caminar al Jardín Hidalgo, la iglesia de San Juan Bautista fundada en el siglo XVI y el famoso y colorido mercado de Coyoacán. Otros puntos de interés en la zona son la casa de Cortés, los barrios de Santa Catarina y La Conchita, la casa azul de Frida Kahlo, la casa de León Trostky, el mueseo de la Acuarela, la Fonoteca Nacional, la casa de Elena Garro, librerías y el centro comercial Oasis. Coyoacán tiene mucho que ofrecer y está muy cerca del emblemático barrio de San Angel.

description:
Luxury penthouse at the most upscale area of charming La Condesa. Beautiful office within private rooftop terrace - enjoy the beautiful sunsets, launch 55" UltraHD TV. Ample closet space, fully equipped kitchen, washing room. 24/7 security guards. Lots of charming cafes and restaurants around. 1 parking. Beautiful views, jacuzzi. Premium mattress king size bed, premium towels. Fastest Wifi 200Mbps. Half a block away from beautiful Parq Mexico and Amsterdam oval. You'll love this place!

The space
Modern furniture and decoration. Very spacious apartment. 170 m2 area.
First floor: Fully equipped kitchen with luxury accessories; Cozy ample living room with balcony; Social bathroom; First office with desk and office ergonomic chair.
Second floor: Ample Bedroom, 49" HD TV, full bathroom, comfortable shower with hot water, roomy closet and balcony with hamoc and two pandurata trees.
Third floor: Wonderful Terrace and the coolest office.

Gue
host_about: I’m a Colombian Spanish entrepreneur who lives in Mexico City. I live in La Condesa with Sara, my girlfriend. We give it all for our guests to have a great experience, and I personally arrange and communicate with guests. When we travel and stay at someone’s place, we take care of it to the highest standard. name: Loft con muy buena ubicación y mucho estilo
description:
About this space

Casa Gabriel CDMX está ubicada en la Colonia del Valle, a unas cuadras del World Trade Center. La zona es tranquila, ideal para caminar y tomar un café al aire libre. Casa Gabriel es un proyecto de restauración, el edificio es antiguo con un toque arquitectónico moderno. El loft comparte con la casa de enfrente un patio abierto en el que puedes disfrutar una bebida, una lectura o una carne asada. ¡Un espacio tranquilo y cómodo dentro de la ciudad!

Guest access
El loft se encuentra en la parte de atrás de una pequeña casa, el acceso es por la puerta principal de la casa, pero tiene un pasillo muy amplio y un pequeño patio compartido

Other things to note
Para nosotros es importante cuidar y aprovechar concientemente los recursos naturales. Por ello tenemos calentador solar. El horario ideal para tomar un baño caliente es después de las 3pm. De cualquier modo, fíjate en el sol!

name: Xochimilco Hermosa Casa Jardín cerca de Trajineras
description:
Espacio bonito, tranquilo, seguro y con estacionamiento privado dentro de la Ciudad de México, rodeado de vegetación y tranquilidad, ubicado en Xochimilco (Actualmente Patrimonio Cultural de la Humanidad ante la UNESCO) a unos metros de las tradicionales trajineras ubicadas en el Embarcadero más grande de Xochimilco.
Ubicada a 10 minutos del Museo Dolores Olmedo, a 200 metros del Bosque de Nativitas (ahí encontrarás paseo a caballo, venta de antojitos mexicanos) y Mercado de plantas Madre Selva

The space
Es una casa de un solo piso que se encuentra dentro de privada de 5 casas totalmente seguro. Cuenta con Roof garden privado ideal para convivencias con carne asada o familiares, así como espacio de jardín. Se encuentra ubicada en una zona rodeada de tienditas y con muy fácil acceso. Está ubicada a unas calles de Avenida Prolongación División del Norte.

Other things to note
Cualquier persona que se aloje o entre de visita a la propieda
host_about:
Excelente anfitrión, me encanta el poder atender con amabilidad y gusto a mis huéspedes. Serio y formal para mis tratos.
Excelente esposo y respetuoso ante cualquier preferencia de los seres humanos.
Me encanta dar respeto y que me respeten. Amo los espacios amplios y las personas amables.

name: CASA TEO by Enrique Olvera
description:
Inspirado en las residencias artísticas, Casa TEO es un espacio creado para fomentar la creatividad y el intercambio de ideas a través de la reflexión y el diálogo, ofreciendo a sus huéspedes un lugar único para realizar estancias y generar proyectos por medio de un programa activo de encuentros y talleres, buscando contribuir al enriquecimiento cultural de México.

The space
El espacio de Casa TEO es totalmente minimalista, preocupados por los detalles y la funcionalidad, su diseño gira alrededor del comedor -una cocina abierta con mesa comunal que invita a compartir- y dos habitaciones, ambas con baño propio, para recibir a residentes y viajeros.

Casa TEO cuenta con una biblioteca, que alberga una serie de libros de gastronomía y temas relacionados a esta, la cual sirve de inspiración para el equipo de trabajo cercano al chef Enrique Olvera.

Other things to note
Casa TEO invita a gente que admira para ofrecer talleres y pláticas

We are happy to welcome respectful and quiet guests that want to treat this house as their own.

neiborhood_overview:
The San José Insurgentes neighborhood limits to the east with Insurgentes Sur, to the north with Avenida Río Mixcoac, to the west with Avenida Revolución and to the south with Avenida Barranca del Muerto. Today, the colony is home to important corporate offices, shops and hotels, as well as the iconic Teatro de los Insurgentes.

In the center of the neighborhood, where the main streets converge, is the Parque de los Insurgentes, better known as Parque de la Bola, because of a fountain with a spherical figure. In this park there is a sculpture by Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla, as well as busts of various writers: Juan de la Cabada, Rodolfo Usigli, Rafael Solana, Luis G. Basurto, José Revueltas, Juan Rulfo, Josefina Vicens and Francisco Rojas González.

I will share with you a guide to the best places to eat, visit and know!

Book now!

Observa con atención las cuatro esquinas y aprecia las casas con su fachada en pancoupé rematadas por dos medallones que en algún tiempo ostentaron las siglas o el escudo familiar. Continúa hacia la Plaza Río de Janeiro y aprecia la copia del David de Miguel Ángel al centro, seguro tu mirada te llamará al Edificio de las Brujas o Río de Janeiro en tabique aparente de estilo inglés y una cúpula en forma de sombrero de bruja de estilo alemán. Observa cómo su basamento y el interior del patio está en estilo Art-Decó realizado por el Ing. Francisco J. Serrano. Es una casa familiar, ideal para familias que vienen a visitar la Basílica de Guadalupe o turistear en CDMX, disfrutar de este hermoso lugar moderno vintage muy bien ubicado, a 900 metros de la Basílica de Guadalupe, a una cuadra del metro bus de Reforma y Centro Histórico, parques cercanos, restaurantes y servicios. Donde tendrás comodidad a un precio accesible por la casa en condominio.

The space
Ubicado entre Calzada de Guadalupe y Misterios, las habitaciones cómodas con acabados modernos, disfruta de la terraza para relajarte con vista a la Cúpula de la Basílica de Guadalupe y la Sierra del Tepeyac

Guest access
Disfruta de los espacios amplios de la casa, las habitaciones silenciosas, terraza techada y al aire libre para tener momentos de relajación y reflexión, donde cada uno de los miembros se sentirá cómodo.

Other things to note
La colonia es muy tranquila y familiar.
La casa es en condominio con otra casa

name: Casita Roma
description:
Entire studio with private terrace in Roma Norte. Beautiful light all day!
The studio is located at the third story of the house, to get there you will have to climb stairs and walk through a part of the house.
Once at the studio you will have all the terrace to yourself, there are some
Acapulco chairs and a hammock for you to relax and enjoy a sunny afternoon.
The listing is located near everything you might need from food, transportation, specialty coffeeshops and more.

The space
The space is currently not suitable for remote working due to the construction next door. I only accept short stays for people visiting Mexico City and that want to enjoy the location, the neighborhood and it’s perks.

name: HERMOSA CASA DE LOS 50' MUY BIEN UBICADA
description:
Beautiful house from the 50s in the San Rafael neighborhood. The house is remodeled with two levels. It is very bright and very well located. It is located at the intersection of Reforma and Insurgentes. It is worth mentioning that the house is very calm and quiet, no noise from outside is heard. Below are the living room, dining room, kitchen, 1 WC and an outdoor patio. On the first floor there are two bedrooms, 1 full bathroom. And above is the rooftop of the house and 1 utility room.

Guest access
You have access to all rooms in the house except one locked upstairs where I put inside my personal staff to leave you much space as possible in your rooms.

Other things to note
Guests agree to take care of the house. Please respect the property and the neighbours. NO PARTY, NO PET.

name: La Palomilla B&B Full House
description:
La Palomilla is a unique seven-bedroom boutique Bed & Breakfast located in the heart of La Roma, one of the safest neighborhoods in Mexico City.
Our house is filled with stories of friendship and Mexican culture. From the vibrant interior design in every floor, to the locally-sourced soap in your room, almost every element of La Palomilla supports a Mexican business or talented artisan.

The space
It’s a 1920s remodeled home that has 7 rooms and is perfect for a family or friend getaway.

Guest access
Terrace, living room and kitchen

Other things to note
We have massages, yoga lessons, holistic therapy, mezcal tastings, and cooking lessons to help you set up. We’ve tried and tested them all.
host_about:
Hi, we are Alessandra, Lalo, Elvia and Gerardo and we love that you´re part of our family!

In Mexico, "Palomilla" refers to your closest group of friends, those who make life worth living. Roma Norte, where our historical building stands, was the hub for our most iconic "Palomillas", artists, writers, and the great thinkers of our history.

Our house is filled with stories of friendship and Mexican culture. From the vibrant interior design on every floor to the locally-sourced soap in your room, almost every element of La Palomilla supports a Mexican business or talented artisan

name: Condesa Charm
description:
Comfort meets charm in this authentic 1930s architectural gem from a long-gone era of Mexico city. With fully renovated interiors and a cheerful Mexican decor, this two story house boasts two full bedrooms plus a studio, two full baths, a kitchen, dinning and living room. Located on a residential street in the heart of the trendy La Condesa neighborhood brimming with restaurants, cafés, and art galleries, this home is a perfect base to explore all that this cosmopolitan city has to offer.

The space
The ground floor has a bright and cheerful living room decorated with traditional Mexican textiles, pottery, and art. The kitchen is small but highly functional, with a stove/oven, sink, full-size fridge, microwave, hot water kettle, french press, and toaster oven. It comes fully equipped with dishware, eating and cooking utensils, pots, pans, and basic condiments.

There are two desks: one downstairs and one upstairs in the studio. Strong and stable WiFi thr

name: Casa Roma
description:
Una acogedora y hermosa casa de tres pisos abre sus puertas para ser tu próximo hogar en la Ciudad de México.

Ubicada en pleno corazón del barrio de La Roma, en una tranquila calle cerrada. Aquí estarás rodeado de lo más local, lo más interesante y lo mejor del barrio, empezando por el popular parque de la Plaza de Río de Janeiro, así como restaurantes, taquerías, cafeterías y tiendas locales.

The space
Al entrar sentirás el ambiente hogareño y sabrás que has llegado a tu segunda casa. La luz natural iluminando cada rincón la hace cálida y una decoración acogedora le dan ese ambiente familiar. Un piano, una chimenea, un mini bar, arte en las paredes y tapetes se entremezclan con objetos contemporáneos. Aquí crearás tus recuerdos de viaje.

name: Casa La Camila Tito
description:
Este lugar tiene una ubicación estratégica excepcional.
Yo hospedaje y viaje será muy fácil de planear, ya que tiene a su alrededor todos los servicios y requeridos para disfrutar tu viaje.
host_about:
Saludos a todos,,, Siempre he creído que la Honestidad, el Orden, la Limpieza, el Amor y la Perseverancia, son las cualidades esenciales para vivir en paz y con éxito, de tal forma, que es lo que ofrezco a mis Huéspedes.

Me gusta la vida sana, SIN vicios, alcohol ni drogas.

Mi lugar favorito es la Playa, en especial, La Riviera Maya. El ejercicio es parte de mi Vida.

Lo que más Amo en la Vida es a mi Hija, Familia, Viajar y poder conocer gente.

Algo que me enorgullece es ser Mexicano, por lo que me encanta nuestra gastronomía, tradiciones, cultura, costumbres y todos nuestros géneros musicales.

Me fascina leer libros de superación personal, de salud o de coaching.

Mi deporte favorito son 3: MMA, Americano y el Triatlón.

Me considero un muy excelente anfitrión que le gusta atender a sus huéspedes, de la manera que me gusta que se me atienda.

Espero que se sientan como en su propia casa y recuerden que los esperamos con los brazos abiertos.

Gracias.
Roger Solano.

Greetings to all ,,, I have always believed that Honesty, Order, Cleanliness, Love and Perseverance, are the essential qualities to live in peace and with success, in such a way, that is what I offer to my Guests.

I like healthy life, NO vices, alcohol or drugs.

My favorite place is the beach, especially La Riviera Maya. Exercise is part of my Life.

What I love most in life is my family, traveling and being able to meet people.

Something that makes me proud is to be Mexican, so I love our cuisine, traditions, culture, customs and all our musical genres.

I love reading books on personal improvement, health or coaching.

My favorite sport is 3: MMA, American and Triathlon.

I consider myself a very excellent host who likes to take care of his guests, the way I like to be treated.

I hope you feel at home and remember that we are waiting for you with open arms.

Thank you.

Roger Solano.

Los baños cuentan con puertas de vidrio y finos acabados, la cocina esta equipada con un sistema purificador de agua potable de alta tecnología, servicio de lavandería (con costo adicional). neiborhood_overview: Chimalistac es una colonia del sur de la Ciudad de México correspondiente a la Alcaldía Álvaro Obregón. Chimalistac está formado por un pueblo -de origen prehispánico- y un fraccionamiento de finales del siglo XIX -establecido en los terrenos de lo que fue la huerta del colegio carmelita de San Ángel. Se caracteriza por la uniformidad y belleza de su conjunto arquitectónico y por sus tradiciones y festividades. Del pasado proviene el trazado irregular de sus calles, muchas de las cuales permanecen empedradas y con escaso tráfico.

neiborhood_overview:
You will stay in Colonia San Miguel Chapultepec, right next to the park, Bosque de Chapultepec. The most iconic park in Mexico City that houses the legendary Castillo de Chapultepec. A central and tree covered area, close by the city's attractions and just a few minutes from exclusive neighborhoods such as Roma, Condesa and Polanco, but being in an unbeatable location coming home to a quiet street.
You'll enjoy cafes, restaurants, art galleries, local shops and workshops...in a walkable area, without having to commute into city traffic.
Here you will hear the unique sounds of an old Mexican “barrio”. You will distinguish the whistle of street vendors selling bread in the morning or tamales at night. The ringing of the bells of the garbage truck, or the famous sound of: “Se compran colchones, refrigeradores, tambores, lavadoras o fierro viejo...” vendors that buy material to recycle. All this will make you immerse yourself deeper into our culture, living as a local.
You

name: Casa Tepeji
description:
This gorgeous 3 floors house was integrally renovated by an architect in 2021 and features a unique design with a patio, a terrace and numerous balconies. There are multiple canopies and large windows that allow all the rooms to be very bright. The colors and custom-designed furniture were carefully curated to celebrate the Mexican culture.

The house is located in a very quiet street of the historic Roma Sur neighborhood and offers walking access to the city’s best restaurants and bars.

La mejor ubicación para conocer la ciudad! Estamos a 1 cuadra del Ángel de la Independencia y Reforma, muy cerca de la Embajada Americana.
La zona está llena de restaurantes y es ideal tanto para el viajero de negocios como el de placer.

We are very lucky to have an unbeatable location! We are a few meters away from El Angel de la Independencia and Reforma Avenue, the most iconic location in the city! We are on a small street in the financial district, very close to many restaurants and bars.

The space
Remodeled house in a great location! There are 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, full kitchen, living room and a beautiful terrace!
The house is designed with our guests in mind, so you will find everything you need such as blender, kettle, coffee maker, oven, microwave, iron, ironing board, a large dinning table and a TV.

We are a few meters away from Reforma, Mexico City’s main avenue and from El Angel de la Independencia. There are plenty of Mexican and International restaurants within walking distance.
Getting to downtown, Roma, Condesa and Polanco takes only a few minutes by car or uber.

Estamos a pocos metros de Reforma, la avenida principal de la Ciudad de México, y a 1 cuadra del Ángel de la Independencia. Hay muchos restaurantes mexicanos e internacionales alrededor, sin embargo estamos ubicados en una calle muy tranquila.
Llegar al Centro, Roma, Condesa y Polanco es muy sencillo desde la casa ya que puedes caminar, tomar el Metrobus o el Turibus sobre Reforma o pedir un uber en minutos.

name: Casa Omac | Colonial house with two patios
description:
Typical colonial house, located in the most picturesque and emblematic street of Coyoacán. The style is reminiscent of Frida Kahlo's Blue House, which is a few minutes' walk away. Organized around a large internal patio, the house has 5 double rooms and can host up to 10 people, making it ideal for groups and families.

The space
Casa Omac is a former 18th century convent transformed into a family home.

In the oldest part of the house, there is a kitchen, a full bathroom, a large dining room and a library that has been converted into a TV room. The bedrooms are located in the blue building. On the first floor, there are two rooms with private bathrooms (Guava and Mango). The other three rooms (Avocado, Pomegranate and Pineapple) are located upstairs and share the same bathroom.

There are two patios in the house - one in the center and one at the back - full of plants and flowers. Both are equipped for eating and relaxing outdoors. In the co

neiborhood_overview: Casa Omac was built in the 18th century when Santa Catarina was a small village on the road that communicated Coyoacán with San Ángel. Today, the house has an unbeatable location, less than 200 meters from the beautiful Plaza Santa Catarina. The most emblematic places in the south of the city are at a walk distance: the Centenario Park in the center of Coyoacán (1km - 15 min), the Fonoteca Nacional (5 min), the Frida Kahlo museum (20 min), the neighborhoods of Chimalistac (20 min) and San Ángel (40 min).

neiborhood_overview:
La Condesa is one of Mexico City’s coolest neighbourhoods.

La Condesa is one of Mexico City’s most fashionable neighbourhoods, attracting locals and travellers alike thanks to its pretty tree-lined avenues and chic hangouts.

The area boasts a cosmopolitan vibe with beautiful parks, designer boutiques, fantastic gastronomy offerings, and a vibrant nightlife among other things. It’s little wonder why so many travellers consider it a quintessential inclusion on any Mexican itinerary.

name: Tiny House en el corazón de la colonia Roma.
description:
Vive una experiencia inolvidable en esta casa única, ubicada en el corazón de la colonia Roma Norte, a escasas cuadras de la fuente de Cibeles. Tiny House es una casita de tres pisos que cuenta con 2 recamaras, 2 baños completos, sala, oficina y un rooftop increíble.

Si deseas rentar el espacio para filmaciones o producción debes avisarnos desde un inicio y se cobrará una tarifa adicional dependiendo del proyecto.

We look forward to welcoming you into the Tiny House family!

The space
Tiny House elegantly brings together old-world charm and effortless, modern living. Following a gut-renovation in 2021, it boasts 2 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, a living room (with a piano), a private office, a full kitchen and bar area, and a private rooftop terrace (with a hot tub and a variety of native plants) where you can relax from the hustle-and-bustle of the city down below. neiborhood_overview:
Bienvenidos a Tiny House, a home for artists and creatives looking for a bohemian experience of Mexico City. We are located in the heart of Roma Norte—a neighborhood teeming with music, art, bars, restaurants and cafes—and just a short walk from Parque México, Parque España, Cibeles Fountain, Bosque de Chapultepec and plenty of public transport options.

Although you would be hard-pressed to find something more centrally-located, the house is set back from the road and remains quiet throughout the day.

neiborhood_overview:
Coyoacán is a bohemian neighborhood full of history, culture and picturesque buildings. You can walk, ride a rental bike or get in a "hop on-off bus" to explore the area.

Coyoacán is famous for its cobblestone streets, plazas, colonial buildings, and cultural landmarks including the Casa Azul (Frida Kahlo), Trotsky museum, watercolor museum, among others.

"El Mercado de Coyoacán" is a market with Mexican street food, Mexican candies, and souvenirs. There is also plenty of nice restaurants, bars and cafes on the plazas.

description:
Town house con excelente ubicación en CDMX. El acceso de la casa te recibe con un vestíbulo que se abre al patio –un árbol de guamuchil y otro de copal-, silenciosa y con diseño. neiborhood_overview:
La Condesa is well known for its large number of cafes, bookstores, restaurants, galleries and boutiques, as well as for its cultural and nightlife. It shares its border and bohemian spirit with Colonia Roma, and together they form the so-called Roma Condesa Cultural Corridor.

In La Condesa there are two emblematic parks of the city:
- Spain Park
- Mexico Park
and additionally:
- Popocatepetl Square with its fountain
- Fountains in the small squares-roundabouts of Avenida Ámsterdam: Citlaltépetl and Iztaccíhuatl

Additional green areas are found in the ridges of Avenida Ámsterdam and the avenues Mazatlán, Campeche, Alfonso Reyes and Benjamín Hill.

name: Casa de época con arte y terraza en Roma/Condesa
description:
Haz un viaje especial y una estadía única en la Ciudad de México en este casa de 1910 remodelada, hasta 8 huéspedes. Vivirás una casa histórica, con privacidad, amplios espacios (200 m2), muchísima luz interior, terraza y acabados de lujo. Tendrás acceso a obra gráfica de artistas mexicanos contemporáneos la cual podrás comprar y coleccionar. Ubicación inmejorable dentro de la roma/condesa. A 5-10 minutos de los parques España y Mexico, Chapultepec, Avenida Reforma, restaurantes, museos y bares.

The space
La casa está catalogada por el Instituto Nacional de Bellas Artes (INBA). Sus espacios son amplios con doble y triple altura. La sala/comedor y el estudio/recámara están orientados al poniente dándoles mucha luz por las tardes. El área común tiene un domo con vista al cielo con mucha luz. Ideal para leer, trabajar o ver la televisión. Con plantas y una sensación de calidez. La terraza de 50 m2 y con iluminación para la noche permite disfrutar del aire libre, ya
host_about: Soy mexicano, empresario, aficionado a la literatura, viajes, arte visual y cultura. Hablo inglés y básico de chino mandarín. Emocionado de poner mi espacio de la Roma/Condesa para que otros lo disfruten y pasen días increíbles en la Ciudad de México.

neiborhood_overview:
Estarás en la mejor zona de la Colonia Roma, en la frontera con el inicio de la Condesa. A cinco y ocho minutos de los parques España, Mexico y Chapultepec y de calles emblemáticas de la colonia como son Avenida Mazatlán, Veracruz, Ámsterdam, Durango.

Es una zona clásica de la Ciudad de México con mucha oferta culinaria, cultural y de entretenimiento. Zona arbolada e ideal para peatones o ciclistas. A media cuadra de la casa esta el mercado de Colima. Típico Mercado de barrio donde podrás encontrar fruta, verdura y comestibles. A un lado de la casa se encuentra el restaurantre Básico, el cual ofrece comida saludable, vegana y vegetariana.

Puedes hacer ejercicio o andar en bicicleta en los parques cercanos, cómo Chapultepec que está a 8 minutos caminando.

Museos importantes del país, cómo son el Arte Moderno, Tamayo y el Museo Nacional de Antropología están a 10-15 minutos caminando o en bicicleta.

La casa está a dos cuadras de El Palacio

name: Chapultepec's Townhouse
description:
"Chapultepec Townhouse" is an unique concept in Mexico City. If you are looking for a real experience in our city, THIS IS YOUR BEST OPTION. "Chapultpec Townhouse" is a brand new house located a few blocks away from Chapultpec's Castle, Condesa, Roma and Reforma

The space
" Chapultepec Townhouse" located in one of the best neighborhoods in Mexico City. The house has 3 floors.

1) First Floor: you will find the dinning room, the kitchen and beautiful living room with a balcony to enjoy the weather of our city,

host_about:
Im a Mexican who loves to travel so decided to rent out my home while im not around. I love Airbnb since its the perfect way to travel and to receive like minded guests. I have prepared a full on home & City Guide with my personal recommendations for food, art galleries, sites, museums & parks this way you will be able to experience Mexico city as a local and not fall into the tourist traps. 
Feel free to let me know what the purpose of your visit is and if you need some extra tips :) 

Please treat my home like you would your own :)

*If you want to know more about the house I was interviewed for a interior design magazine to talk about my home  the title of the publication is "Blending Modern with Vintage in This Stunning Mexico City  Home" you can find it on the internet. Below the full article:

BLENDING MODERN WITH VINTAGE IN THIS STUNNING MEXICO CITY HOME

Located in Mexico city’s stylish San Miguel Chapultepec neighborhood, Santiago Vertiz first moved into his 2006-built home ten years ago.

At the time, Santiago didn’t own furniture and slept on a mattress in the empty space – an image in stark contrast to the harmonious blend of modern vs vintage we now see. Vertiz spent years searching for pieces that inspire him, whilst highlighting his Mexican culture.
Fascinated by pre-Columbian cultures and inspired by childhood memories of his grandparents’ houses, many antique pieces fill the house, as well as colourful original modern art, handicrafts and textiles from Mexico and Guatemala.

Nature plays an important role throughout the home, and an entire wall of glass doors opens to the patio, seamlessly blending the indoors with the outdoors. Says Vertiz, “Plants play a very important role in life and in my home. They are the protagonists that bring life, change, and color.”
Santiago’s mission has been to recover, collect, restore, and redesign furniture and other pieces that inspire him, while working with the house’s unique architectural features to amplify its height and to bring life to the space.

What attracted you to your home?
Mexico City can be very hectic, you can easily spend half of your life in traffic. I felt it was a luxury to be able to walk to places without using a car.
I knew I wanted to live in a central location, close to the classic neighborhoods – Condesa, Roma and Polanco are some of the most well-known, but also in high demand. A friend introduced me to San Miguel Chapultepec, which is a residential neighborhood making it quiet, safe and strategically located. It’s across the street from Bosque de Chapultepec and home to many artists and galleries.
Secondly, I was excited by the architectural project. The architect’s goal was to make a town house project resembling a loft, instead of a classical building. There are actually ten identical houses with spacious, double-height ceilings overlooking a private terrace.
When I discovered the space, it had already been built, but I was able to modify the size of the terrace space, and since the view is very important to me, we made a front wall to allow plants to grow in.

Did you have a vision for your home?
I wanted my house to be a place I felt comfortable in, that I could enjoy and feel relaxed. I didn’t want to have a party house – as I said to an old roommate, “My house is my temple”.
I had to improvise and play around a lot with the location of certain pieces, so there was trial and error involved. I would stay up at night thinking of new things I could do to the house – it was a lot of fun!

How did your fascination with pre-Columbian cultures influence the design of your home?
My maternal grandparents came from Merida, Yucatan and had deep knowledge of Mayan cultures. My grandfather would tell us tales of his many visits into the jungle and his friendship with archeologist Alberto Ruz Lhuillier. Not only was he present in the discovery of the Pakal tomb, but he actually helped by providing some of the machinery needed to uncover the tomb. My oldest uncle, a boy at the time, took the first pictures ever of the tomb. I’ve inherited a deep admiration and respect for the Mayas and their communities.
One spring break my parents took us on a road trip, passing through Veracruz into Chiapas, and visiting different ruins along the way. We camped out in the middle of the jungle, next to the Usumacinta river on the border of Mexico and Guatemala. We walked some distance to the ruins of Yaxichilan, and in another location camped with a Lacandon Community, reliving the experience that my grandfather once had.
When I visit a region, anywhere in the world, I value the natives’ culture and appreciate the hard work and beauty that goes into their handcrafts.

La colonia Cuauhtémoc esta muy bien ubicada, en unos minutos puedes llegar a la Roma, Condesa, Chapultepec, Polanco o al Centro Histórico. Aunque la casa está ubicada en una calle tranquila y pequeña, basta con caminar una calle para estar en la Avenida Reforma, la más importante de la ciudad.

Conéctate a un espacio que evoca con nostalgia al Coyoacán del pasado, que te invita a meditar y tomar un respiro del estrés del día a día

Dispondras de mi alojamiento, una casa al clasico estilo de Coyoacán lleno de tradicion.
La tarifa e insumos de limpieza cubre 7 noches. para estadias de mayor duracion, deberas acordarlo previamente conmigo via la plataforma de airbnb.

Cuenta con una habitación con cama king size y dos con cama individual.

name: Casa cerca de Polanco, Reforma y Centro en CDMX
description:
Casa muy céntrica dentro de la Ciudad de México. Es un alojamiento sencillo con todo lo necesario para disfrutar de una estancia en la ciudad. A unos minutos del Centro Histórico, Polanco o Reforma.

La casa es antigua, por lo que pueden existir elementos como la cocina, contactos eléctricos, pisos, muebles, etc. Que tengan desgaste por el tiempo, sin embargo no impiden su funcionalidad.

The space
Casa independiente de 200 metros cuadrados. Con doble altura, amplios espacios, dos pisos, cuatro habitaciones, dos baños completos, cocina integral y pequeño patio. Capacidad máxima para 8 personas. Cuenta con 5 camas (entre individuales, matrimoniales y king size) *No cuenta con sala-comedor*

Guest access
La casa se encuentra en la colonia Tlaxpana, colonia popular (No turística). En la calle de Tlaloc, a dos cuadras de Circuito Interior, tres cuadras de la Calzada México-Tacuba y tres cuadras de la Av. Marina Nacional.

No

name: Stunning 19th Century Townhouse in Roma Norte
description:
19th Century Townhouse at the heart of Roma Norte, one of the most exciting and sought after neighborhoods in Mexico City, full of history, art, entertainment, cafés, bars and hundreds of dining options. Less than a block away from Alvaro Obregon avenue, but quiet and peaceful.

The space
The house has 4 bedrooms: the master bedroom has a king size bed and a full bathroom and dressing, the second bedroom two twin beds (with a bathroom with a bathtub just outside), the third room has a double bed, and the fourth room is in the ground floor and has a full private bathroom.The living room is very spacious with a balcony with a street view, and the dining room is just next to it. The kitchen is also very spacious with a breakfast area. The house also has a small foyer, an interior patio and a small office. Ideal for large families or groups of friends.

neiborhood_overview: Roma Norte, the center of Mexico City's artistic and culinary spirit, is home to cycling hipsters and a growing number of young professionals. Its leafy central avenue, Álvaro Obregón, is lined with eclectic restaurants, sidewalk bars, and restored mansions; one of these houses the cultural center Casa Lamm. Food lovers often visit the international food stalls of Mercado Roma, while the avenues are lined with street art.

neiborhood_overview:
"Las Lomas" dates back to the 1920s, when it was founded with the name Chapultepec Heights. Home to some of the biggest mansions in the city and many high-net-worth individuals, it has gained a reputation of exclusivity. Its main entrance is through Paseo de la Reforma which is the most emblematic street in Mexico City.

"Las Lomas" is the safest neighborhood in Mexico City. Close to main tourist attractions including Polanco and Chapultepec. The neighborhood offers a variety of restaurants and activities.

name: Villa Uh-May: huge house w/private rooftop Condesa
description:
Casa Uh-May takes its name from a mayan town in Quintana Roo where the artisans handcrafted most of its decoration.
Beautifully decorated with 7 bedrooms, private rooftop, a patio, and private parking, you'll feel in an oasis of peace, but steps away from everything you want to enjoy in Mexico City.

The space
The layout of this house is like no other, which makes part of it's magic but it's also important for you to understand.
Ground floor: first you have the garage adjacent to the patio, the enter to the house and you'll find a king size bedroom, living room, dining room, half bathroom (toilet) and the kitchen.
Floor 1: 3 king size bedrooms, the main bathroom, and outside you'll fin the laundry and an outdoor shower.
To go to the top floor you'll find 3 ways, a door in the hall next to the main bathroom, the black stairs in the middle room (perfect for when it's raining), a door in the first room where you can find the laundry too.
Top

name: Fantástica casa biblioteca Octavio Paz @Coyoacan
description:
En el centro de Coyoacán, mejor ubicación, imposible. Silenciosa, cautivadora, espaciosa, rodeada de verde. Esta preciosa y tranquila casa fue donde estuvo en sus últimos años la Revista Vuelta del premio Nobel de literatura Octavio Paz. Antigua casa que tiene más de un siglo de construida.

The space
Cuenta con vestíbulo de entrada y un medio baño. Un patio rodeado de helechos con mesa para comer al exterior. Sala, comedor, cocina y tres recámaras. Una con cama queen, TV, baño completo y un estudio en el segundo piso con Wifi. Dos recámaras más, una con cama King Size y otra con cama matrimonial y un escritorio, que comparten baño completo, TV y Wifi. Cuarto de lavado con lavadora, mesa de planchar y plancha con vapor.

Guest access
La casa es de uso de los huéspedes. No comparten zonas comunes con nadie.

Other things to note
INDICACIONES PARA EL USO DE LA CASA


SEGURIDAD.
Por razones de seguridad
host_about:
Me gusta estar con mi familia, en el mar y la montaña, viajar a lugares lejanos de culturas diferentes. Escuchar música, ir a teatro y a cine, leer. Me gusta ver el amanecer y atardecer.
Dejar la casa que alquilo como me gustaria que dajaran la mía.
"Al mal tiempo, buena cara"

name: Lujoso Palacio Boutique en el corazón de Condesa
description:
La Casa de las Campanas fue construida en 1904, Inspirada en la arquitectura francesa, con acabados de la época. Hospédate en un palacio boutique, en el corazón de la condesa. Su biblioteca en vez de contar historias a través de sus libros, lo cuenta con una colección de más de 700 campanas de los 5 continentes.

Para tu comodidad tenemos internet de 100 MBPS

Cuenta con 4 habitaciones que te harán vivir en una época clásica, llena de historia.

The space
Tres habitaciones están dentro de la casa y una habitación está ubicada en otra área donde está la biblioteca y el espacio de trabajo.

Guest access
Toda la casa es para uso privado de tu reservación, no debes compartir con nadie más

Other things to note
Condesa es uno de los vecindarios más divertidos y seguros de la ciudad.

El Palacio Boutique está ubicado entre dos hermosas colonias: la Roma y la Condesa, dos barrios con gran valor

name: Deluxe Penthouse in Roma Norte with Scenic Views
description:
Located in Roma Norte, you're in the heart of the most cherished and vibrant district in CDMX, and close to an array of wonderful restaurants, bars, and shops.

This incredible penthouse 2 bedroom in a brand new, luxury building with 24/7 security is JUST what you need. Enjoy a spacious living space with modern appliances, a laundry room, large windows that allow plenty of natural, radiant sunlight and best of all, an incredible view from the penthouse unit. Enjoy access to a spacious roof top.
host_about:
At Casa Azul, our casa is your casa.

"Las Lomas" also known as Chapultepec Hills is the most exclusive neighborhood in Mexico city. You'll find larger homes that are more spread out in this area of the city vs compact areas like Polanco and Condesa.

You'll be surrounded by mansions, embassies and high net worth individuals/celebrities. It is a wealthy and highly secure neighborhood that is close to the best tourist spots CDMX has to offer.

Situated in a cul-de-sac between two of CDMX most sought after locations - Polanco and Santa Fe.
Easy access from Reforma Ave in a centric zone.
10 minutes away from the Convention/Expo center in Santa Fe.

Located in Central Coyoacan, this is traditional Mexican house. It is an oasis in the big city. This house is ideal for 6 persons and it is possible to rent the house next door for additional 6 guests.

The space
High ceilings, large rooms and common spaces. This house has beautiful natural lighting through the day. Thick walls absorb sun light and release the heat at night for a perfect cozy night.

Other things to note
For long stays we can offer cleaning services once a week.

neiborhood_overview:
The neighborhood of Coyoacan was home to explorer Hernán Cortés and was used as a resting place thank to the beautiful climate.

Eventually, the neighborhood developed to be the beautiful colonial place full of colorful buildings, cobbled streets, and beautiful churches.

It also has some of the best markets in the city. In a day out in Coyoacán you can eat, drink, and feast your eyes around every colorful corner.

neiborhood_overview: Coyoacán is a bohemian neighborhood full of history, culture and picturesque buildings. You can walk, ride a rental bike or get in a "hop on-off bus" to explore the area.   Coyoacán is famous for its cobblestone streets, plazas, colonial buildings, and cultural landmarks including the Casa Azul (Frida Kahlo), Trotsky museum, watercolor museum, among others.   "El Mercado de Coyoacán" is a market with Mexican street food, Mexican candies, and souvenirs. There is also plenty of nice restaurants, bars and cafes on the plazas  (Coyoacan, conchita, Santa Catarina)..

We are a couple in love and we have managed to become a team. We love being with friends, long talks with new people and we live inspired by our three sons Bruno, Lara and Mila!

We love to take the hospitality level beyond expectations and receive people in our house all the time. Now we do it in several properties carefully accommodated for you, in strategic places in one of the most incredible cities in the world: Mexico City.

Will be a truelly pleasure to host you!

Va a ser un verdadero placer hospedarlos!

host_about:
We are a couple in love and we have managed to become a team. We love being with friends, long talks with new people and we live inspired by our three sons Bruno, Lara and Mila!

We love to take the hospitality level beyond expectations and receive people in our house all the time. Now we do it in several properties carefully accommodated for you, in strategic places in one of the most incredible cities in the world: Mexico City.

Will be a truelly pleasure to host you!

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••

Somos un matrimonio enamorado y hemos logrado volvernos un equipo. Que nos encanta estar con amigos, charlar con gente nueva y vivimos inspirados por nuestros tres hijos Bruno, Lara y Mila!

Nos encanta llevar el nivel de hospitalidad mas allá de lo esperado y recibir gente en nuestra casa todo el tiempo. Ahora lo hacemos en varias propiedades acomodadas cuidadosamente para uds, en lugares estratégicos de una de las ciudades mas increíbles del mundo: Ciudad de México.

Va a ser un verdadero placer hospedarlos!

name: Art deco Condesa 5 BR house with a Rooftop
description:
Get ready to live Mexico City at its best, not just by staying in La Condesa, one of its most iconic neighborhoods, but by staying at the very heart of it.
Our house is in prime location, and it maintains its original art deco design. After a year long restoration, you will also have all that modern comfort offers.
Designed for longer stays, enjoy a lovely rooftop, a dedicated room with gym equipment, a patio with a grill, and ample space to enjoy or work throughout the house.

The space
The house is planned in two stories, with a rooftop on the third level. The first level has common areas (living room, main hall, kitchen, dining room, patio, half bathroom). The second level has four bedrooms and two full bathrooms. The rooftop is a large open space, with two rooms and a full bathroom; one room is a bedroom, and the other is equipped as a gym.

Guest access
The whole of the house is at your disposal, including patio, rooftop, and e
host_about:
I'm a Mexican husband, father and business owner looking forward to meeting many worldly and interesting people. I love to travel, know our city and enjoy our neighborhood (I was born, raised, and again live in Condesa, in CDMX). I practice sports as a hobby, enjoy reading, good food, and music, as well as my family and friends.
As of now, I've much enjoyed our guests as I've had the opportunity to meet people from all around, with both similar and different lifestyles than my own, and it has been definitely enriching. I look forward to hosting you, and sharing with you our house and our city.

name: Historic Villa Condesa + Top Design Kitchen
description:
Historic Villa Condesa is a 1936 huge and comfortable independent house with high ceilings, open spaces in hardwood floors. It was renovated recently to bring it up to today´s needs incorporating new comfort to a historic household.

The whole group will be comfortable in this spacious 505 Sq meter / 5,435 square foot and unique space overlooking one of the most iconic and beautiful tree lined avenue and with a private garden and 2 balconies.

The space
High ceilings and spacious atmosphere with a modern twist to enjoy with the whole group. Partially serviced fir comfort and relaxation during any stay.

Guest access
All the villa is accessible except the service quarters and storage spaces in the fourth floor.
host_about:
Relaxed coffee lover, foodie, art and photography, hiking and some sports now and then.

Passionate about Mexico.

Condesa connoisseur. 

Wake up early and enjoy the day. 

New friends are always welcome. Whatever you need i'm here to host you and your friends!

name: Hermosa casa estilo mexicano, 3 recamaras
description:
Céntrica y amplia casa en calle cerrada con vigilancia las 24 horas; 3 recámaras y family room con sofá cama; 3 y 1/2 baños, cocina súper equipada y roof garden. A un par de cuadras del

The space
La casa consta de 3 plantas. Planta baja: Sala, comedor, cocina, cuarto de lavado, medio baño, patio y garage. Planta media: 3 recámaras, 3 baños y family room. Planta alta: roof garden con asador. La chimenea del roof garden es decorativa (no funcional).

Guest access
Puedes acceder a toda la casa, con excepción de la puerta que da al patio y el área del cuarto de servicio. Ambas están cerradas con llave.

neiborhood_overview:
Modern skyscrapers combine with elegant mansions from the early 19th century. This incredible house stays in a unbeatable location, on a parallel street to the iconic Paseo de la Reforma Avenue, right across from the Angel de la Independencia Monument, near to restaurants that range from open-air taquerias to chic international restaurants.

From its ancient Aztec history to Spanish
influence and contemporary design, the
Cuauhtémoc neighborhood is brimming with culture. The streets are lined with open-air taquerias, local boutiques, and historical museums at the heart of the sprawling Bosque de Chapultepec park.

You’ll stay also a short 5-minute walk from the Mexican Stock Exchange Buildind, next to the U.S. Embassy and luxury hotels like Sheraton and St Regis.

The historic center is a 10-minutes drive away, also Polanco, Condesa and Roma Neighborhoods. 10/10 location!

host_about:
We are a couple in love and we have managed to become a team. We love being with friends, long talks with new people and we live inspired by our three sons Bruno, Lara and Mila!

We love to take the hospitality level beyond expectations and receive people in our house all the time. Now we do it in several properties carefully accommodated for you, in strategic places in one of the most incredible cities in the world: Mexico City.

Will be a truelly pleasure to host you!

••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••

Somos un matrimonio enamorado y hemos logrado volvernos un equipo. Que nos encanta estar con amigos, charlar con gente nueva y vivimos inspirados por nuestros tres hijos Bruno, Lara y Mila!

Nos encanta llevar el nivel de hospitalidad mas allá de lo esperado y recibir gente en nuestra casa todo el tiempo. Ahora lo hacemos en varias propiedades acomodadas cuidadosamente para uds, en lugares estratégicos de una de las ciudades mas increíbles del mundo: Ciudad de México.

Va a ser un verdadero placer hospedarlos!

name: Glamping Xochimilco
description:
Enjoy this experience in the only glamping in Xochimilco. Break the routine surrounded by nature, learn more about this unique ecosystem in the world, spend a magical night without losing the comfort of a hotel. It's not just a lodging, it's an experience! We want you to have a complete experience, we have optional activities such as visits to agricultural chinampas, kayaking at dawn, as well as food service for your comfort, book them!

The space
We are in the heart of ecological Xochimilco, where biodiversity conservation is sought, and local life is developed through organic agriculture, scientific and cultural outreach workshops, even soccer fields and social events.
We have 6 finely decorated tents, equipped with soft double beds and cozy bedding, in an exclusive and spacious chinampa (floating gardens), surrounded by the mystical Xochimilco canals.

neiborhood_overview:
Polanco is one of the favourite areas for visitors or tourists in Mexico City, this is due to its level of security, its proximity to everything: shopping malls, local author/designer businesses, and international luxury brands on the famous Avenida Presidente Masaryk. In turn, it has a beautiful green lung surrounded by different attractions such as an artificial lake, an aviary, an open-air theater - El Ángela Peralta, a playground for children and various activities that take place daily in the famous Lincoln Park. neiborhood_overview:
Coyoacan is an area of Mexico City known for its cobbled streets, art galleries, colourful buildings and artisan markets. With plenty of leafy parks, it feels like you’ve been whisked away to a peaceful village. It’s hard to imagine you’re in a city of 22 million!

The village feel is hardly a surprise because Coyoacan was indeed once its own independent town. Cuidad de Mexico grew and engulfed it, yet it retained its old-fashioned charm.

name: Habitación del Yogui. Cama, Yoga, Barre, Arte.
description:
Nuestro Airbnb se encuentra en la planta alta de Espacio Bengala: Co-Wellness Center, es un mono-espacio con todo lo necesario para una estancia confortable y sin complicaciones. Tu hospedaje incluye dos clases de Yoga, Barre o cualquiera de nuestras disciplinas durante tu estancia. Nuestro espacio es mucho más que un estudio, es una experiencia única de salud, paz y bienestar durante tu visita a la CDMX. Disfruta de la sencillez de este alojamiento tranquilo y con una ubicación inmejorable.

The space
A183 Espacio Bengala es un Co-Wellness Center que cuenta con un Estudio de Yoga y Espacio de Meditación.

Te ofrecemos un mono-espacio (32.40m2) con dormitorio para dos personas con cama Queen size y un sofá cama que puede recibir a un niñ@ pequeño. La cabina de regadera y lavabo estan integrados al espacio. Cuenta con una cocineta equipada con estación de tostador, cafetera y parrilla, utensilios básicos de cocina, y una mesa donde comer o trabajar.

neiborhood_overview:
Polanco es una de las zonas más exclusivas de la Ciudad de México.

Este barrio ofrece una enorme gama de restaurantes, bares, boutiques y tiendas que van de lo más exclusivo a opciones más relajadas e igualmente sorprendentes. Se encuentra cerca de múltiples corporativos, siendo así una zona ideal para quien hace un viaje de negocios. También cuenta con una importante actividad cultural con museos como el de Antropología e Historia, Jumex, Tamayo, Soumaya. Polanco se ubica a corta distancia del Parque y Castillo de Chapultepec y la nueva Torre de Luz. También muy cerca del Auditorio Nacional y el Centro Cultural del Bosque donde puedes ver lo más relevante de las artes escénicas contemporáneas del país.

name: Cozy home in San Angel
description:
House located in the heart of San Ángel, in one of the most beautiful neighborhoods in Mexico City, on a cobbled street, just a few blocks walk from downtown San Ángel, the Diego Rivera and Frida Kahlo Studio Museum, the traditional Bazaar del Saturday, the Church of San Jacinto, the Casa del Risco Museum, the Ex-convent of Carmen, the San Ángel Inn Restaurant (one of the most iconic in the city), as well as countless restaurants, shopping malls and boutiques.

The space
The house has three bedrooms each one with an en-suite bathroom, the main room with a King Size bed, the second bedroom has two single beds, the third bedroom is a loft with a single bed, it also has a full kitchen, dining room, breakfast area, living room, half bathroom and a study, as well as a beautiful garden and a garage for up to three vehicles.

name: Hidden Gem in La Condesa
description:
Welcome to our Oasis tucked away in the best neighborhood in the best city in the world!

The downstairs offers an expansive living/dining room area that leads into a lush private back patio. Off the kitchen, you'll find a cozy breakfast nook.

The mezzanine is as relaxing as could be with a wrap around couch and high end TV (swivel wall mount).

Upstairs offers a Primary bedroom (King) guest room (Queen) with an ensuite bathroom, a private office with pullout couch, and full hallway bath.
host_about:
Hi, I live in San Francisco in a home that I list on Airbnb.  I try to stay as active as possible and travel whenever I can. 

As an Airbnb host myself, while traveling and staying in other people's homes I know the value of being a good guest and do everything I can to be easy to deal with and to respect/appreciate whatever space I'm staying in.

While hosting travelers in San Francisco, I try to put myself in their shoes and do my utmost to provide everything they need for the best stay possible.

name: Hip, Refined House (negotiable)
host_about:
Soy un argentino apasionado y aventurero. Llegué a México para un viaje de un mes después de trabajar en la filamación de 5 largometrajes consecutivos y me enamoré de este increíble país, por lo que nunca me fui. Dos meses después volví a enamorarme, pero esta vez de una de sus bellas mujeres, y me casé con Karina. Ten en cuenta que si vienes a México, es posible que nunca te vayas!

I am a passionate and adventurer Argentinean. I came to Mexico for a one-month road trip after working in five feature films shootings in a row and I fell in love with this amazing country, so I never left. Two months later I fell in love again, but this time to one of its beautiful women, and I married Karina. Be aware that if you come to Mexico, you might never leave!

neiborhood_overview:
A quiet lifestyle, a lot of history and a relaxed cultural environment, are some of the things you could enjoy living in Coyoacán. It was in this magical neighborhood that Hernán Cortés established the First City Hall, marveling at its beautiful landscapes with abundant springs, orchards, fields and multicolored gardens.

Due to its magical atmosphere, its abundant vegetation, its tranquility and its provincial characteristics, numerous personalities of the stature of the writers José Juan Tablada and Rubén M. Campos, the pioneer researcher of Mexican art Manuel Toussaint came to reside in the old town of Coyoacán , the teacher and great chronicler Salvador Novo, the outstanding painter José Chávez Morado, the renowned artists Dolores del Río, Emilio “Indio” Fernández, Frida Kahlo, Manuel Álvarez Bravo, Diego Rivera, and the political exile León Trotsky, among many others.

neiborhood_overview:
La colonia Escandon es una zona muy buena a tan solo 5 min de la Condesa a pie, con restaurantes y bares a la vuelta.
No sólo es el sabor de la alta cocina gourmet , sino el reconocido ambiente que se respira, las mesitas al aire libre, aroma a buen café, músicos callejeros y gitanos que leen la suerte.
Ahí puedes encontrar boutiques muy exclusivas de diseñadores, ropa de moda, formal o casual.
Encuentras galerías, librerías, tiendas de antigüedades, cines, teatros, pintores y artistas, que han hecho de la Condesa su hábitat.
Para tu casa y oficina, hay múltiples posibilidades de equipo, iluminación, mobiliario y decoración. Diseño gráfico, Industrial, digital, etc.

neiborhood_overview:
It is in a popular low middle-class neighborhood, surrounded by a huge established food market, bakeries, small restaurants, "taquerias" (tacos) hair style saloons, "tortillerias" (tortillas), shoe repair shop, convenient stores, pharmacies, inexpensive family doctors, and bars, all around 2 to 3 blocks from the house. You will feel as if you were in a small town in the middle of the very urban Mexico City.
The food market is a folklore whole experience to walk inside. Everything is fresh, it is a very different experience for those that only buy groceries in urban super markets. You can buy fresh "tortillas", "salsa", "quesadillas", "flautas", "barbacoa" (sheep meat) , and all the typical food Mexicans eat. Best of all at very low prices, for being in low middle-class neighborhood.

You can buy fresh "tortillas", "salsa", "quesadillas", "flautas", "barbacoa" (sheep meat) , and all the typical food Mexicans eat. Best of all at very low prices, for being in low middle-class neighborhood.

description:
A peaceful terraced house in the centre of La Roma, trendiest Mexico City neighbourhood. The perfect place to have a pleasant stay, with a courtyard and a rooftop garden. A few blocks away to basically everything you'll need from restaurants, cafés, markets, shops to transportation.

On the ground floor there's a dining room, a comfortable living room, a kitchen, and a toilet. On the 1st floor there's two bedrooms, a bathroom, and a small studio with a balcony overlooking the patio.

The space
The house was built in the 1930s and was renovated a couple years back. It preserves its unique Roma style.

On the ground floor there's a dining room for up to 6 people, a comfortable living room, a small but fully-equipped kitchen with an oven, a private patio and a toilet.

On the upper floor there's two bedrooms with wooden floors and plenty of sunlight, a bathroom, and a small studio with a balcony overlooking the patio.

host_about: Soy una mujer sencilla, trabajo muchas horas por día y un poco por necesidad, pero también por el gusto de recibir y conocer a gente de otros países me propuse alquilar mi departamento. description:
Disfruta de la sencillez de este alojamiento tranquilo y céntrico. Coyoacán es uno de los lugares con mayor tradición cultural en la CDMX, Casa Xochipili está dedicada al Dios de las flores, todos los cuadros de flores fueron pintados por mi mamá. La casa fue construida por el reconocido actor mexicano Héctor Godoy, el amor y el cuidado por los detalles como la talavera del baño y de la cocina son únicos. El pequeño jardín interior está decorado por un mosaico diseñado por Aurora Reyes.

Guest access

The neighborhood of Coyoacan was home to explorer Hernán Cortés and was used as a resting place thanks to the beautiful climate.
